description: Toggle auto delivering of items.
Causes damage to bounce back on Tiny's attackers. Melee enemies that attack Tiny have a chance of being stunned. The proc chance improves with each level in Grow.
language.lore: Melee warriors tend to find attacking the Stone Giant largely ineffective.
notes: The damage and stun occur when an attack lands.

description: Cause roots to burst from the ground, immobilizing the target enemy unit and causes them to take more damage from attacks. Enemies can still move and attack while entangled.
Riki fades into the shadows, becoming invisible. When Riki attacks, he becomes visible. Grants bonus movement speed
language.lore: Riki comes for you.
notes: Riki won't auto attack enemies while invisible.
Illusions of Riki will play Backstab animations, but not deal any bonus damage.
Bonus damage from Backstab can't be evaded.

description: Releases a visible Torrent in a random area around you once every 0.25 for 5.0 seconds. Spawns in within 1100 range of you.
language.lore: A hundred leagues of dry land couldn't keep these seas at bay.

description: Leaps backward and dodges incoming projectiles.
language.lore: Sproink is as Sproink does.

description: Resets Clockwerk's ability cooldowns and grants him bonus movement and attack speed for a duration. Clockwerk becomes stunned after the duration runs out.
language.lore: Rattletrap understands the limitations of his armor. Just as he understands the risks of pushing past them in times of need.

description: Ejects the swallowed allied hero inside of you.
language.lore: Allies emerge forever changed.

description: Lycan bites an ally, granting them Shapeshift properties. Lycan and the bitten target gain 30% Lifesteal and share Lifesteal with each other as long as they are within 1200 range of each other.
language.lore: Does this bite look infected?

description: Dispels negative buffs and grants you bonus attack speed. Has an increased effect during the night.
language.lore: The Goddess of the Moon smiles upon her kin.

description: Creates vines towards the target location. Vines slow down and deal damage to enemies that walk through. Vines deal 50% more damage if they touch a tree. Does half damage to creeps.
language.lore: The Protectors don't often come into vision; their natural state being nestled within their leafy brethren.

description: Channeling. Drow releases a flurry of arrows in continuous salvos, hitting enemies for extra damage and applying longer duration Frost Arrows. Lasts up to 1.75 seconds.
language.lore: In the ranger's youth, learning to fire multiple arrows at once was considered a distracting frivolity. In the war of the Ancients, such technique has become strange necessity.

description: Puck instantly attacks all enemies upon casting Phase Shift, within attack range + 200.

language.displayName: Lil' Shredder Uses Your Attack Damage

description: Roshan calls a group of Roshlings to aid him.
Roshan launches a number of slow moving fireballs at all nearby enemies.
Performs a quick Omnislash.
Enemy units in range of Sand Storm have their movement speed slowed by 40% and miss 40% of their attacks.

language.displayName: +7% Hunter In The Night Movement Speed
+20 Finger of Death Damage Per Kill
Skeleton Walk Exit Summons A Burning Army Skeleton
+15% Storm Surge and Unlocks Max Speed

description: End your Focus Fire early.
Damage done by direct attacks.
Improves all attributes per point spent
Burns an opponent's mana on each attack. Mana Break deals 50% of the mana burned as damage to the target. Mana Break has 50% effect if caused by illusions.
language.lore: A modified technique of the Turstarkuri monks' peaceful ways is to turn magical energies on their owner.

description: Short distance teleportation that allows Anti-Mage to move in and out of combat.
language.lore: In his encounter with the Dead Gods, Anti-Mage learned the value of being elusive.
notes: You can use Blink to dodge incoming projectiles.

description: Increases Anti-Mage's resistance to magic damage.
language.lore: Years of meditation and obsession with revenge have hardened Anti-Mage's skin against mystical opponents.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes Spell Shield to passively block and reflect a targeted spell once every %scepter_cooldown% seconds.
notes: Stacks multiplicatively with other spell resistance sources.

description: For each point of mana missing by the target unit, damage is dealt to it and surrounding enemies.  The main target is also mini-stunned.
language.lore: After bringing enemies to their knees, Anti-Mage punishes them for their use of the arcane arts.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases stun duration. Mana Void kills cause the enemy's highest cooldown ability to take longer to cool down upon respawning.
notes: Damage is calculated based on the primary target's mana, but applied to all enemies within the area of effect.

description: Axe taunts nearby enemy units, forcing them to attack him, while he gains bonus armor during the duration.
language.lore: Mogul Khan's warcry taunts opponents into engaging in an unconquerable battle with the Axe.

description: Enrages an enemy unit, causing it to be slowed and take damage over time until it kills another unit or the duration ends. Axe gains movement speed for each unit affected with Battle Hunger, half speed from creeps.
language.lore: Ordinary heroes cannot withstand Mogul Khan's rage for battle, such that it injures them until it is satisfied.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes Battle Hunger to be an area of effect ability, and reduces the damage output of affected enemy units.
notes: Destroying buildings will also remove the debuff.

description: When attacked, Axe has a chance to perform a helix counter attack, dealing pure damage to all nearby enemies.
language.lore: Axe is the only reinforcement this army needs.
notes: Counter Helix triggers when the attack hits.

description: Axe spots a weakness and strikes, instantly killing an enemy unit with low health, or dealing moderate damage otherwise. When an enemy hero is killed with Culling Blade, its cooldown is reset, and Axe and nearby allied units gain bonus movement speed.
language.lore: Mogul Khan is the embodiment of battle and fury, launching into a gruesome fatality against those who dare engage the Axe in combat.

description: Feasts on the vital energies of an enemy unit, healing Bane and dealing damage.
language.lore: Atropos finds no greater pleasure than to harvest the fear he creates.
language.aghanimDescription: Decreases cooldown, cast point, and makes Brain Sap pierce Spell Immunity.

description: Bane's abilities enfeeble his targets, lowering the affected unit's magic and status resistances.
language.lore: Each tendril of fear that Atropos weaves increases the vulnerability of his victims to arcane and unknown arts.

description: CHANNELED - Grips an enemy unit, disabling it and causing heavy damage over time, while stealing mana every 0.5 seconds based on the unit's maximum mana.
language.lore: Victims of Atropos are frequently torn apart by vivid conjurations of their own nightmares.
notes: Fiend's Grip will disable and drain mana from Spell Immune units, but not damage them.

description: Puts the target enemy or friendly Hero to sleep. Sleeping units are awakened when damaged. If the target was directly attacked, the Nightmare passes to the attacking unit. Bane can attack nightmared targets freely.
language.lore: A stolen prowess from the goddess Nyctasha is to put his prey into forever sleep.
notes: In the first second of Nightmare, the unit is invulnerable.
Bane can wake himself from Nightmare.
On cast, replaced with Nightmare End: Ends all ongoing Nightmares on any affected units.

description: Drives you into a bloodthirsty rage during which you attacks faster and deal more spell damage at the cost a percentage of your health per second. Provides half attack speed to allied heroes.
language.lore: Strygwyr shares his animalistic thirst for bloodshed.
notes: Bloodrage can be cast on yourself or an enemy units.

description: Bloodseeker baptizes an area in sacred blood. After 2.9 seconds the ritual completes, causing any enemies caught in the area to take damage and become silenced.
language.lore: The Flayed Twins are ever willing to aid those who spill blood upon the field of battle.
notes: Total time is a 2.6 second delay plus a 0.3 second cast time.

description: Bloodseeker is invigorated by the wounds of his enemies, restoring some life when he kills an enemy unit. Also gains bonus movement speed when an enemy hero's health falls below 75%, with the bonuses increasing as their health falls further. If an enemy hero's health falls below 25%, he will also gain vision and True Sight of that hero. Bonuses stack per hero. Unlocks max movement speed for Bloodseeker.
language.lore: Strygwyr becomes frenzied when blood is spilled.
notes: Not triggered by Illusions.
Max movement speed and attack speed bonuses occur when an enemy's health is at or below 25%.
Effects linger for 4.0 seconds if a target dies.

description: Causes an enemy unit's skin to rupture. If the unit moves, it takes damage based on the distance moved.  The damage is dealt through spell immunity.
language.lore: When the Bloodseeker hunts you, injuries become fatalities.
language.aghanimDescription: Grants %max_charges_scepter% charges to Rupture with a %charge_restore_time_scepter% seconds replenish time.

description: Adds a freezing effect to Drow's attacks, slowing enemy movement and dealing bonus damage. Slow lasts 1.5 seconds.
language.lore: Ice-encased arrows pierce the silence, chilling their victims to the core.
notes: The slow duration is refreshed on successive casts.

description: Stops all enemy units in a target area from casting spells.
language.lore: Traxex is rather fond of the tranquility of physical combat, calling on her Drow heritage to end the incantations of opposing magi.
notes: Doesn't stop usage of items.

description: Adds bonus damage to the physical attack of allied, ranged Hero units based on a percentage of Drow's agility.  Affects creeps for 30 seconds when cast.
language.lore: Traxex' time spent alone in the forests of her Drow home has allowed her to teach other archers how to improve their bow skills.

description: Drow's experiences in battle grant her a chance to launch arrows with incredible accuracy and effectiveness. Pierces through the enemy's defenses, ignoring their base armor. Grants Drow and nearby ranged heroes with bonus agility based on Drow's current agility. This ability is disabled if there is an enemy hero within 400 range.
language.lore: The Drow Ranger is the epitome of archery prowess.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes Drow Ranger's attacks to splinter on the target, hitting nearby units with normal attacks that deal reduced damage.
notes: Marksmanship procs have true strike.

description: Slams the ground with a mighty totem, creating an impassable ridge of stone while stunning and damaging enemy units along its line.
language.lore: The Nishian totem splits the world to its core with tectonic force.
notes: Creeps will wait for Fissure to disappear. They will not attempt to walk around it.
Fissure is not blocked by Linken's Sphere.

description: Empowers Earthshaker's totem, causing it to deal extra damage and have 75 bonus attack range on the next attack.
language.lore: Raigor's gorilla strength can destroy mountains.
language.aghanimDescription: Enchant Totem becomes a %distance_scepter% range ground target ability, causing Earthshaker to jump in the air and land at the target spot, casting Enchant Totem there.  Self-casting the ability will behave in the original form, without jumping.
notes: Bonus damage is based on base damage and that given by primary attribute.
Self-cast with Scepter will make it behave in the non-Scepter form, without jumping.

description: Causes the earth to shake underfoot, adding additional damage and stuns to nearby enemy units when Earthshaker casts his abilities.
language.lore: The earth trembles beneath the mighty footsteps of Raigor.
notes: Using items does not trigger Aftershock.

description: Shockwaves travel through the ground, damaging enemy units.  Each enemy hit causes an echo to damage nearby units. Real heroes cause two echoes.
language.lore: Tectonic plates crack, mountains fold, and foes are crushed by the Echo Slam.

description: Gives Juggernaut a chance to deal critical damage on each attack.
language.lore: The last remnant of his heritage's commitment to bladework, Yurnero ensures that the style is remembered.

description: Causes a bladestorm of destructive force around Juggernaut, rendering him immune to magic and dealing damage to nearby enemy units.
DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
language.lore: Yurnero's renowned katana techniques are feared by warriors and sorcerors alike.
notes: You can use items during Blade Fury.
Juggernaut can still perform attacks while in Blade Fury. However, only units that are not affected by Blade Fury, such as wards or structures, will take damage from these attacks.

description: Summons a Healing Ward which heals all nearby allied units, based on their max health. The Healing Ward moves at 350 movement speed after being summoned. Lasts 25.0 seconds.
language.lore: Of the rituals learned at the Isle of Masks, tending wounds with a bit of voodoo magic has proven to be quite useful.
notes: The healing ward can be controlled.
Multiple healing wards do not stack.

description: Juggernaut leaps towards the target enemy units, and then slashes the target and other nearby enemy units at an increased attack rate. Juggernaut is invulnerable for the duration.
language.lore: 'The fruits of discipline; with practice comes strength.'
language.aghanimDescription: Adds a new ability: Swift Slash. Performs a mini omnislash for a short duration.
notes: You can use items during Omnislash.
Can target Spell Immune units.
Omnislash applies a basic dispel to Juggernaut on cast.

description: Summons a rising torrent that, after a short delay, hurls enemy units into the sky, stunning, dealing damage and slowing movement speed.
language.lore: An ancestral rush of water explodes from the center of the world, called upon by the Admiral.
language.aghanimDescription: Adds a new ability: Torrent Storm. Continuously releases visible Torrents around you.
notes: The initial bubble effect is only visible to allies and provides vision in fog of war.
Units tossed in the air will be stunned and still able to be attacked.

description: Kunkka's legendary sword grants increased damage and cleaves a large area of effect in front of him for a single strike.
language.lore: A lost Claddish soul inhabits Kunkka's trusty Tidebringer, empowering it to destroy demons of the Cataract.
notes: Cleave damage goes through spell immunity.

description: Targets a friendly or enemy Hero, marks their position with an X, and returns them to it after several seconds.  Kunkka can trigger the return at any time during the duration. Lasts twice as long on allied heroes.
language.lore: The Admiral's set of arcane abilities includes some that can be used for battle as well as entertainment.
notes: If the target becomes Spell Immune after the cast, the target will not return to the X after the duration.
Interrupts channeling spells.

description: Returns the marked hero to the X.

Summons a ghostly ship that sails through the battle before smashing apart, damaging and stunning all enemies caught near the wreckage. Allied heroes touched by the Ghostship are given a swig of The Admiral's Rum, receiving bonus movement speed and a delayed reaction to incoming damage.
language.lore: The final ship of the Claddish Navy is nothing but a phantom, but it is all too real to the enemies of the Admiral.
notes: Damage dealt after Rum wears off is non-lethal and can never kill a hero.
Actual area of effect of ship's collision is larger than the boat itself.
The boat has a movement speed of 650.

description: Lina channels the breath of a dragon, sending out a wave of fire that scorches every enemy in its path.
language.lore: In the scorched barren of Misrule, Lina learned to manipulate the fiery breath of the Desert Wyrm as a form of entertainment.
notes: Dragon Slave can hit units up to 1225 units away.

description: Summons a column of flames that damages and stuns enemies.
language.lore: Lina's essence allows her to focus the sun's energies, causing air to combust at will.
notes: Light Strike Array will destroy trees in its area of effect.

description: Grants bonus attack and movement speed each time Lina casts a spell. Stacks with itself. Lasts 10 seconds.
language.lore: Dancing flames embody Lina's playful nature, bringing out her true blazing self.
notes: Duration refreshes each time a new spell is cast.
Using items does not trigger Fiery Soul.

description: Fires off a bolt of lightning at a single enemy unit, dealing massive damage.
language.lore: The air around Lina becomes so intensely torrid that it scorches a foe that comes too close with white-hot lightning.
language.aghanimDescription: Changes Laguna Blade's damage type to Pure, and allows it to slice through spell immunity.
notes: Laguna Blade has a 0.25 delay before the damage is applied after the spell is cast, allowing certain abilities to avoid the damage.

description: Rock spikes burst from the earth along a straight path. Enemy units are hurled into the air, then are stunned and take damage when they fall.
language.lore: The Demon Witch exercises his demonic covenant, opening a fissure from hell.
notes: The spikes move at 1600 / 1600 / 1600 / 1600 units per second.

description: Transforms an enemy unit into a harmless beast, with all special abilities disabled.
language.lore: Lion is compelled to share his transfiguration, twisting the essence of those who oppose him.
notes: Instantly destroys illusions.
The target will have a base movement speed of 140, but buffs granting maximum movement speed won't be disabled.

description: CHANNELED - Absorbs the magical energies of a target enemy unit by taking mana from it every second.
language.lore: Lesser magi are nothing more than a source of magical restoration for the Demon Witch.
notes: Instantly destroys illusions.

description: Rips at an enemy unit, trying to turn it inside-out. Deals massive damage and grows stronger with each life it consumes.
language.lore: Lion's disfigured hand is also the source of his greatest power, capable of flooding victims with malefic force.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases damage. Decreases cooldown. Finger of Death hits all units in a small area.
notes: Finger of Death has a 0.25 delay before the damage is applied after the spell is cast, allowing certain abilities to avoid the damage.
Finger of Death only gains damage if the enemy hero dies within 3 seconds of being affected by Finger of Death.

description: Fires a long-range arrow with deadly precision, which stuns and damages the first enemy unit it strikes. The stun duration ranges from 0.01 to 3.5 / 4 / 4.5 / 5.0 seconds, with bonus damage up to 180 added, based on the distance the arrow travels to its target. Instantly kills the first non-ancient creep it hits.
language.lore: Lunar energies make the Princess of the Moon's arrows more deadly than most.
notes: For every 150 distance the arrow travels, the stun duration upon impact increases by 0.5 seconds, and the bonus damage added increases by 14.
Sacred Arrow can hit invisible units.

description: Turns Mirana and all allied heroes invisible and grants bonus movement speed. If a hero is revealed, invisibility will restore after the fade delay as long as Moonlight Shadow's duration has not expired.
language.lore: Her tenure with Selemene allows Mirana to eclipse the ground, wrapping her allies in a cloak of shadows.
notes: Units affected will not auto attack enemies.
Spell Immune allies will be affected.

description: Mirana leaps forward into battle, empowering herself with a ferocious roar that grants bonus attack and movement speed. Speed bonus lasts 2.5 seconds.
language.lore: None can fail to recognize Mirana's iconic white beast in the heat of battle.

description: Calls down a wave of meteors to damage nearby enemy units. The closest enemy unit to Mirana in a 425 radius will be struck a second time for 75% of the damage.
language.lore: The Goddess breaks the strata to empower her Princess in the time of need.
language.aghanimDescription: Passively triggers Starstorm every %interval_scepter% seconds. Does not trigger if the enemy doesn't see Mirana.
notes: Starstorm is not blocked by Linken's Sphere.
Starstorm cannot hit invisible units.
Starstorm will choose a new target for the second star if the first died before impact.

description: Morphling dissolves into liquid and surges forward, damaging enemy units in his path.  Morphling is invulnerable during Waveform.
language.lore: A torrential flood takes enemies by force.

description: Launches a surge of water toward an enemy unit, dealing base damage plus additional damage based on Morphling's agility times a multiplier.  If Morphling's agility is 50% higher than strength, the maximum agility multiplier is used.
Also puts Adaptive Strike (Strength) on a 3 second cooldown.
language.lore: The Morphling calls upon his elements to crush his opponents with waves.
notes: Projectile moves at 1150 speed.

description: Morphling shifts its form, pulling points from Strength and pouring them into Agility. The process is reversible.  Additional points in Attribute Shift increase the rate of stat change.  Passively grants bonus Agility.
language.lore: Shifting water makes it difficult to discern the nature of Morphling.
notes: Attribute Shift can't convert stats from items.
Leveling up Agility Gain will also level up Strength Gain.

description: Morphling shifts its form, pulling points from Agility and pouring them into Strength. The process is reversible.  Additional points in Attribute Shift increase the rate of stat change.  Passively grants bonus Strength.
language.lore: Shifting water makes it difficult to discern the nature of Morphling.
notes: Attribute Shift can't convert stats from items.
Leveling up Strength Gain will also level up Agility Gain.

description: Morphling changes his form to match the targeted enemy, gaining their basic abilities with reduced mana cost. Can be toggled for the duration of the ability.
language.lore: Staring into Morphling produces a reflection that mimics the beholder.
language.aghanimDescription: Allows targeting allied heroes. While Morphed, you gain Cast Range increase.
notes: You can't target yourself with Morph.

description: Toggles Morphling's form between his own and the replicated enemy.

Shadow Fiend razes the ground directly in front of him, dealing damage to enemy units in the area. Adds a stacking damage amplifier on the target that causes the enemy to take bonus Shadow Raze damage per stack.
language.lore: Nevermore's trademark for harvesting souls.
notes: Stack duration refreshes on stack gain.

description: Shadow Fiend razes the ground a short distance away from him, dealing damage to enemy units in the area. Adds a stacking damage amplifier on the target that causes the enemy to take bonus Shadow Raze damage per stack.
language.lore: Nevermore's trademark for harvesting souls.
notes: Stack duration refreshes on stack gain.

description: Shadow Fiend razes the ground a longer distance away from him, dealing damage to enemy units in the area. Adds a stacking damage amplifier on the target that causes the enemy to take bonus Shadow Raze damage per stack.
language.lore: Nevermore's trademark for harvesting souls.
notes: Stack duration refreshes on stack gain.

description: Shadow Fiend steals the soul from units he kills, gaining bonus damage. On death, he releases half of them from bondage.
language.lore: Harvested souls swirl in and out of the Abysm, empowering the Shadow Fiend to increase the size of his collection.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases max souls.
notes: Denies and neutral creeps also provide bonus damage through Necromastery.

description: Shadow Fiend's presence reduces the armor of nearby enemies.
language.lore: Even being near Nevermore eats away at one's soul.
notes: Stacks fully with other armor reduction abilities and aura.

description:
Shadow Fiend gathers his captured souls to release them as lines of demonic energy. Units near Shadow Fiend when the souls are released can be damaged by several lines of energy. Any unit damaged by Requiem of Souls will be feared and have its movement speed reduced for 0.8 seconds for each line hit. Lines of energy are created for every soul captured through Necromastery.

Requiem of Souls is automatically cast whenever Shadow Fiend dies, regardless of its cooldown.
language.lore: The captured souls of those past slain are released to ravage their former allies.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases Necromastery Max Souls and causes Requiem of Souls to return back to Shadow Fiend. The wave back to Shadow Fiend deals less damage, but heals Shadow Fiend for all the damage it dealt.
notes: One line is generated from Shadow Fiend for every 1 souls in his possession, for a maximum of 18 lines (23 lines with Scepter).
The movement reductions from Requiem of Souls go through spell immunity.
Fear and movement slow do not apply when if the Requiem was released on death.

description: Sends a magical spirit lance to a target enemy unit that damages and slows, while summoning an illusory phantom to attack the unit.
language.lore: Azwraith's proficiency at spearing his family's meal of fish is proving quite useful in the battlefield.
notes: Nearby illusions will mimic the cast animation.

description: Phantom Lancer briefly vanishes from the battlefield. After 1 second, Phantom Lancer and any of his nearby illusions reappear at a random position within the targeted location, along with two additional doppelgangers. Extends duration of all illusions. The two added doppelgangers have different properties: one takes normal damage and deals none, while the other takes 500% bonus damage and deals -80 less damage.
DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
language.lore: Dread Magus Vorn's death imbued the Phantom Lancer with the ability to bend and fracture all spectrums of light.
notes: This ability can be used to dodge projectiles, and dispell debuffs.
Trees near a reappearing unit will be destroyed.
Phantom Lancer and his allies can see which illusion is the 100% damage illusion.

description: Phantom Lancer has a chance to fracture his presence, creating an illusion of himself. Illusions also have a chance to fracture further. Illusions created from Phantom Lancer last for 8 seconds, while illusions created from other illusions last 4 seconds.
language.lore: Each of Azwraith's lance attacks feels like two from a normal warrior; or three; or four...
notes: Illusions created by Juxtapose will attack the target that the ability was triggered upon.

description: When targetting an enemy for an attack, Phantom Lancer quickly charges into range, gaining a temporary agility boost upon reaching the target. Phantom Lancer's illusions also have this ability.
language.lore: Azwraith knows that on the field of battle, speed can mean everything.
language.aghanimDescription: Removes cooldown and minimum distance.
notes: If the attack order is cancelled, the movement speed bonus is lost.
Rush movement speed is 800.

description: Puck launches a magic orb that floats in a straight path, damaging enemy units along the way. At any point, Puck may teleport to the orb's location using Ethereal Jaunt.
language.lore: The playful Faerie Dragon delights in confusing others, vanishing and reappearing where unexpected.
notes: The Illusory Orb grants unobstructed vision around its location while it travels.
Jaunting to the Orb will disjoint projectiles.

description: Teleports Puck to a flying Illusory Orb.
Puck teleports to the target location and releases a burst of faerie dust that deals damage and silences enemy units nearby.
language.lore: With a mischievous grin, Puck spreads its enchanted powder which disrupts magical flow.

description: CHANNELED - Puck briefly shifts into another dimension where it is immune from harm.
language.lore: With a quip and flash, Puck returns to the alien dimension from whence it came.
notes: Puck retains collision size while under the effects of Phase Shift.
Issuing any action will cancel Phase Shift.
Puck is invulnerable during Phase Shift.

description: Creates a coil of volatile magic that latches onto enemy Heroes, stunning them for 0.5 seconds, damaging and leashing them. If the enemy hero stretches the coil by moving too far away, it snaps, stunning and dealing additional damage.
language.lore: The Faerie Dragon sows confusion by forcing its enemies to vividly dream about their own mortality.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases damage from coil breaks, increases coil duration, coil break stun goes through spell immunity.

description: Gives Pudge increased magic resistance, as well as bonus strength that increases each time Pudge kills an enemy Hero or it dies in his vicinity.  Flesh Heap is retroactive, meaning it can gain charges before it is skilled, which then become active.
language.lore: The Butcher gives new meaning to the words 'meat shield.'

description: Launches a bloody hook toward a unit or location. The hook will snag the first unit it encounters, dragging the unit back to Pudge and dealing damage if it is an enemy.
language.lore: The Butcher's hook is a symbolic nightmare, its curved blade a frightening reminder of his slaughterous intent.
notes: Interrupts channeling spells of the primary target if it's an enemy.
Meat Hook hits invisible units.
Meat Hook can go through trees, cliffs, buildings, ancient units and Roshan.
Meat Hook can drag friendly units, but they won't be damaged.
Meat Hook can hit and drag runes to Pudge, refunding the Hook's mana cost.

description: A toxic cloud that deals intense damage and slows movement--harming not only enemy units but Pudge himself.
language.lore: A foul odor precedes a toxic, choking gas, emanating from the Butcher's putrid, ever-swelling mass.
notes: Using Rot doesn't interrupt channeling.
Rot hits invisible units.
If Pudge is silenced, he can't deactivate Rot if it's activated.

description: CHANNELED - Pudge chows down on an enemy unit, disabling it and dealing damage over time. Pudge gets healed for the same amount he damages. Lasts longer on creeps.
language.lore: 'When I'm through with these vermin, they'll be fit for a pie!'
language.aghanimDescription: Reduces cooldown and allows targeting an ally to swallow them and heal them for %scepter_regen_pct%%% of their max health per second. The ally can exit whenever they want by issuing a command.
notes: If a unit becomes invisible while Dismembered, it will still be under the effects of Dismember.

description: Creates a cone of ethereal energy that strikes multiple enemy units.
language.lore: Originally used to open shows with the travelling con-man, Rhasta's lightning display shocks adversaries in more ways than one.
notes: Can hit secondary targets up to 1000 distance away.

description: Transforms an enemy unit into a harmless creature, disabling their attacks and abilities.
language.lore: Rhasta often ended performances by turning himself into a chicken - now, the humiliation is shared.
notes: Instantly destroys illusions.
The target will have a base movement speed of 100, but buffs granting maximum movement speed won't be disabled.
Hex disables damage block.

description: CHANNELED - Magically binds an enemy unit so that it cannot move or attack, while dealing damage over time.
language.lore: A self-defense incantation, Rhasta developed shackles after his master was slain in the Bleeding Hills.

description: Summons 10 Serpent Wards to attack enemy units and structures. The Wards are immune to magic.
language.lore: Snake charming was a big part of the Shadow Shaman's act; now Rhasta can empower the snakes to do his bidding.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes Serpent Wards to have split shot, attacking two units for full damage. Increases attack range of Serpent Wards.

description: Releases a wave of energetic plasma that grows in power as it expands, but also zaps on contraction, slowing and dealing damage to enemy units caught in its path. Damage and slow increases with distance from Razor. The Plasma Field hits each unit twice, once each direction.
language.lore: The Lightning Revenant rules the Underscape with plasmatic power.

description: Creates a charged link between Razor and an enemy Hero, stealing damage from the target and giving it to Razor. Allows razor to attack while moving with the link active.
language.lore: Razor's polarity channels electricity into his being, draining the power of his opposition.
notes: The link is broken when either unit dies or the distance between them becomes 250 units greater than Static Link's cast range.
Can target Spell Immune units.

description: Passively increases your movement speed.
language.lore: Merely approaching the Lightning Revenant is rewarded with shock therapy.

description: A powerful lightning storm strikes out at enemy units with the lowest health, dealing damage and reducing their armor.
language.lore: Ride the lightning.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes Eye of the Storm to strike two different units instead of one and can damage structures.  When striking buildings, it will only target towers, barracks, and the Ancient.
notes: Each blast targets the lowest health enemy unit within range.
Eye of the Storm will prioritize striking static linked heroes.
Successive casts of Eye of the Storm will stack.

description: Wraith King sears an enemy unit with spectral fire, dealing damage and stunning, then dealing damage over time and slowing the target.
language.lore: Ostarion calls on his damned lineage, laying waste to his opponents.
notes: If Wraith King has summoned skeletons, casting Wraithfire Blast on a target will order all of the skeletons to attack that target.

description: Nearby friendly heroes restore health based on the damage they deal when attacking enemy units. Has 50% effect on ranged allied heroes. Does not affect allied creeps.
attributes: Nearby friendly heroes restore health based on the damage they deal when attacking enemy units. Has 50% effect on ranged allied heroes. Does not affect allied creeps.%Description%
Wraith King's blade drains his enemy's essence to feed his aura.%Lore%
Vampiric Aura lifesteal has 50% effect on ranged Heroes.%abilitydraft_note%
Stacks additively with other sources of Lifesteal.%Note0%
language.lore: Wraith King's blade drains his enemy's essence to feed his aura.
notes: Stacks additively with other sources of Lifesteal.

description: Wraith King passively gains a chance to deal bonus damage on an attack. Every two kills on an enemy unit adds a skeleton charge. Skeletons respawn once when killed.
language.lore: One blow to crush a foe.
notes: Summoned skeletons will automatically attack any unit targeted by Wraithfire Blast.

description: Wraith King's form regroups after death, allowing him to resurrect when killed in battle. Upon death, enemy units in a 900 radius will be slowed.
language.lore: Conspirators against the Wraith King wonder why he never stays dead.
language.aghanimDescription: If a nearby allied hero is slain, they will be transformed into a wraith and have their death delayed for %scepter_duration% seconds.
notes: Wraith King won't revive if he doesn't have enough mana.
If Wraith King has an Aegis and Reincarnation off cooldown, Reincarnation will trigger first.
Revives with full HP and Mana.
Credit for allies whose death was delayed will go to whoever struck the original killing blow.
Wraith Delay affects Wraith King's actual deaths, not Reincarnate deaths.

description: Sends a swarm of winged beasts to savage enemy units in front of Death Prophet.
language.lore: Krobelus' many trips to the grave gather a flock of the damned.
notes: Can hit units up to 1110 range away.

description: Prevents enemy units in a target area from casting spells.
language.lore: Peering into the veil of her opponent's demise, Krobelus sees a silent future.
notes: Doesn't prevent usage of items.

description: Unleashes evil spirits to drain the life of nearby enemy units and structures. At the end of the spell's duration, Death Prophet is healed in proportion to the damage dealt. Lasts 35 seconds.
language.lore: Over time, the banshee remnants of her previous lives return to haunt the present.
language.aghanimDescription: Whenever an enemy is affected by your spells or when you attack an enemy, a ghost will fly out, slow and hit the enemy for bonus its usual damage then return to you with life.
notes: Radius represents the area in which the spirits will acquire targets around Death Prophet.
Spirit damage isn't reduced by damage block abilities.

description: Sven unleashes his magical gauntlet that deals damage and stuns enemy units in a small area around the target.
language.lore: The Rogue Knight's iron gauntlet, taken from the school of his father, strikes his foes to their core.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases cast range and transports you along the storm hammer, attacking every enemy on impact.

description: Sven strikes with great force, cleaving all nearby enemy units with his attack.
language.lore: The Vigil Knights still seek to reclaim the stolen Outcast Blade from Sven, a weapon capable of cutting wide swaths through lesser warriors.
notes: Cleave damage goes through spell immunity.
The cleave damages a circular area in front of Sven.

description: Sven's Warcry heartens his allied heroes for battle, increasing their armor and movement speed. Lasts 8 seconds.
language.lore: Calling a few lines from the Vigil Codex fortifies Sven's obedience to his rogue code. So poetic!

description: Sven channels his rogue strength, granting bonus damage for 40.0 seconds.
language.lore: With the strength that shattered the Sacred Helm, the Rogue Knight stands unopposed in melee combat.
notes: The bonus damage is based on base damage and the primary attribute of Sven.

description: Creates an explosively charged image of Storm Spirit that lasts 12.0 seconds and will detonate and deal damage if an enemy unit comes near it.
language.lore: Raijin Thunderkeg's duality allows him to admire himself in shocking fashion.
notes: Remnants take 1.0 second to materialize after the spell is cast.
Remnants grant unobstructed vision for their duration.
The explosion actually hits units in a 260 radius, but will only be triggered in 235.

description: A vortex that pulls an enemy unit to Storm Spirit's location.
language.lore: Raijin's thunderous, boisterous energy often draws others into an electrifying situation.
language.aghanimDescription: Electric Vortex affects all enemies within a radius around Storm Spirit.

description: Casting a spell creates an electrical charge, which is released in a burst on Storm's next attack, dealing damage and slowing nearby enemies.
language.lore: Pow!  Zip!  Zap!
notes: Using items doesn't trigger Overload.
Overload charges do not stack.

description: Storm Spirit becomes volatile electricity, charging across the battlefield until he depletes his mana or reaches his target. The activation mana cost is 30+ 8% of his total mana pool, and the cost per 100 units traveled is 10+ 0.65 of his total mana pool. Damage is expressed in damage per 100 units traveled.
language.lore: The Storm is coming in.
notes: Abilities and items can be used while traveling.
This ability will destroy trees.
Storm Spirit is invulnerable during Ball Lightning.

description: Sand King burrows into the ground and tunnels forward, damaging and stunning enemy units above him as he resurfaces.
language.lore: Crixalis often lies in wait, burrowing under the surface to ambush his adversaries.
language.aghanimDescription: Adds Caustic Finale poison to heroes hit by your Burrowstrike and increases its cast range. Does not apply Caustic Finale to illusions.

description: Sand King creates a fearsome sandstorm that damages enemy units while hiding him from vision.  The effect ends when Sand King leaves the area.
language.lore: Some say Crixalis is a mirage; his carapace appearing then vanishing between the whirling sands of the Scintillant Waste.
notes: Sand Storm can be used to dodge projectiles.
Sand King briefly becomes visible upon attacking or using spells while in Sand Storm. Sand King will become invisible again in 0.7 seconds.

description: Sand King's attacks inject a venom that causes enemy units to move more slowly and to violently explode when it dies.
language.lore: An injection from Crixalis makes one brittle and as dry as the arid wastes, subject to implosive demise.

description: CHANNELED - After channeling for 2.0 seconds, Sand King sends a disturbance into the earth, causing it to shudder violently. All enemies caught within range will take damage and become slowed. Each subsequent pulse increases the radius of damage dealt.
language.lore: Many an explorer was lost to the quicksands of the Scintillant Waste.
notes: The pulses are centered on Sand King, not where he first casted the spell.
The pulses have gradually inreasing radius: 275 / 325 / 375 / 425 / 475 / 525 / 575 / 650 / 675 / 700.

description: Bombards an area with rocks, continously doing small intervals of damage and stun to enemy units. Avalanche does 3x damage to units being tossed.
language.lore: Inanimate rock becomes animate when called by the Stone Giant.

description: Grabs the nearest unit in a 275 radius around Tiny, ally or enemy, and launches it at the target unit or rune to deal damage where they land. If the tossed unit is an enemy, it will take an extra 30% damage.
language.lore: Tiny's gargantuan stature allows him to catapult even the sturdiest of warriors.
notes: You can toss allies, but they don't take damage.
Toss deals 33% of its damage to buildings.

description: Grabs a tree to whack enemies on the head for a limited number of attacks. Grants bonus attack range. Attacks deal more damage and fully splash on units along the way. The tree can be thrown, to deal your attack to a unit at a distance.
language.lore: Sticks and stones break all the bones, with structures sure to follow.
language.aghanimDescription: Grants new ability: Tree Volley. Tiny throws random trees within range towards the targeted aoe.
notes: The cooldown begins when the tree is thrown.

description: Tiny gains craggy mass, increasing his attack damage, and armor, while slowing his attack speed.
language.lore: Watching a hill become a mountain is awe-inspiring - especially if the mountain begins laying waste to adversaries.
language.aghanimDescription: Grants you a new channeling ability, Tree Volley. Tiny throws a random tree within range towards the targeted aoe. Deals Tiny's attack damage plus a bonus to enemies in that area with each tree thrown.

description: Hurls a bolt of lightning that leaps through nearby enemy units.
language.lore: Arc Lightning is Zeus' favorite spell to use against puny mortals.

description: Calls down a bolt of lightning to strike an enemy unit, causing damage and a mini-stun. When cast, Lightning Bolt briefly provides unobstructed vision and True Sight around the target in a 750 radius. Can be cast on the ground, affecting the closest enemy hero in 325 range.
language.lore: A shocking punishment for rebellious heathen.
notes: You can interrupt channeling spells and items with this ability.

description: Zeus shocks any enemy hit by his abilities, causing damage proportional to their current health.
language.lore: The air crackles with static when the Thundergod walks the world.
notes: The damage from Static Field is dealt before the damage from the used spell.
Using items doesn't trigger Static Field.

description: Strikes all enemy heroes with a bolt of lightning, no matter where they may be.  Thundergod's Wrath also provides True Sight around each hero struck.  If an enemy hero is invisible, it takes no damage, but the True Sight is still created at that hero's location.
language.lore: The Lord of Heaven smites all who oppose him, near or far.
language.aghanimDescription: Grants a new ability, Nimbus, creating a cloud that automatically casts Lightning Bolt on nearby enemies.

description: Slardar slithers ahead, moving significantly faster and passing through units. Slardar has unlocked max speed and grants movement speed while in the river.
language.lore: As Slardar has made the transition from the Deeps, it has been necessary to use his powerful tail for sprinting instead of swimming.
language.aghanimDescription: Provides additional HP Regen, Armor and Status Resistance while in a puddle or in the river.
notes: Activating this skill doesn't interrupt channeling abilities.

description: Slams the ground, stunning and damaging nearby enemy land units.  After the stun, the affected units are slowed.
language.lore: A swift crush of might and water breaks even the toughest of defenses.
language.aghanimDescription: Whenever Slardar casts Slithereen Crush, he creates a puddle of water that is considered a river for movement and bonuses.

description: After 3 attacks, your next attack will bash the target.
language.lore: Thieves of the wealth of the Deep Ones meet the brutality of the Slithereen Guard in melee combat.
notes: Does not stack with Skull Basher.

description: Reduces enemy armor to amplify physical damage and provides True Sight and vision of the targeted unit, revealing invisibility.
language.lore: Even the strongest armor counts for little when left to the brine of the sea.

description: Summons a gush of water to damage an enemy unit, reducing their movement speed and armor.
language.lore: During his championship of the Sunken Isles, Leviathan gained mastery over the open sea.
language.aghanimDescription: Gush becomes a ground targeted wave ability that affects enemy units in a line.  Decreases cooldown.

description: Thickens Tidehunter's hide to passively block a portion of any incoming physical attack damage. The hide also removes negative status effects if the damage taken crosses a threshold.
Does not stack with items that provide Damage Block.
DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
language.lore: Claddish navymen tell tales of a mighty sea-faring beast that suffered spear and sword but continued to lay waste to the fleet.
notes: Only damage from player owned sources is counted towards debuff removal.
The counter will reset if no player owned damage is taken for 6.0 / 6.0 / 6.0 / 6.0 seconds.
Kraken Shell removes most debuffs, even if they are generally not purgable.

description: Tidehunter swings his mighty anchor to attack and deal bonus damage to nearby enemies and reduce their attack damage.
language.lore: Stolen from one of Admiral Kunkka's flagships, Leviathan's heavy anchor proves useful as a melee weapon.
notes: Anchor Smash works on all Ancient creeps except for Roshan.

description: Slams the ground, causing tentacles to erupt in all directions, damaging and stunning all nearby enemy units.
language.lore: Calling to the abyssal god Maelrawn has resulted in entire armadas being lost at sea.
notes: Ravage will hit invisible units.
Ravage waves move outwards at a speed of 725.

description: Fires a magic missile at an enemy unit, stunning and dealing damage.
language.lore: A simple Skywrath technique, the magic missile is Shendel's primary tool for vengeance.

description: Vengeful Spirit's presence increases the ranged attack range and primary attribute of nearby friendly units. Spawns a Strong Illusion of Vengeful Spirit when she dies that lasts until it is killed or Vengeful Spirit revives.
language.lore: Although they may not share her undying passion for revenge, allies do draw on her fanaticism in combat.
notes: Vengeance Illusion keeps providing the Vengeance Aura after Vengeful Spirit's death.
Strong Illusions are not instantly killed by spells.

description: Vengeful Spirit lets loose a wicked cry, weakening the armor of enemies and giving vision of the path ahead.
language.lore: Shendel's haunting voice hints at her approaching vindication.

description: Instantaneously swaps positions with a target Hero, friend or enemy.  Nether Swap interrupts channeling abilities on the target.
language.lore: Martyrdom is a small price to pay for vengeance.
language.aghanimDescription: After a Nether Swap, enemies around Vengeful Spirit are Feared.
notes: Works on Spell Immune units.
Trees near Vengeful Spirit and the target will be destroyed when the spell is cast.
Channeling spells are interrupted by Nether Swap.

description: A burst of damaging frost slows enemy movement and attack rate in the targeted area.
language.lore: The air temperature around Rylai drops rapidly, chilling all around her to the core.

description: Encases an enemy unit in ice, prohibiting movement and attack, while dealing damage over time. Lasts 10.0 seconds on creeps level 6 or lower.
language.lore: Rylai channels winds from the Blueheart Glacier, imprisoning attackers in thick blocks of ice.
notes: Frostbite is considered a root.

description: Gives additional mana regeneration to all friendly units on the map. This bonus is increased for Crystal Maiden.
language.lore: Cold temperatures promote the essence of magic, causing Rylai's presence to allow spell usage in abundance.

description: CHANNELED - Surrounds Crystal Maiden with random icy explosions that slow enemies and deal massive damage. Grants bonus armor while channeling. Lasts 10 seconds.
language.lore: Once the place of her exile, Icewrack has become an anchor for Rylai's frigid onslaught.
language.aghanimDescription: Applies Frostbite to any unit that has been standing in the Freezing Field for over a set amount of time.
notes: The slow is applied on all enemies in the radius, even if they aren't hit by an explosion (lasts 1.0 second).
Explosions occur every 0.1 seconds.

description: Shackles the target to an enemy unit or tree in a line directly behind it. If no unit or tree is present, the stun duration is reduced to 0.75 / 0.75 / 0.75 / 0.75.
language.lore: Windranger's variety of bow skills includes an arrow with thick ropes attached to encumber any escaping target.
notes: This spell can shackle two enemies together, stunning them both.
Can shackle the target to an enemy unit or tree at most 575 behind the target.
Shackleshot can be disjointed.

description: Windranger charges her bow for up to 1.0 second for a single powerful shot, which deals more damage the longer it is charged. The arrow damages enemies along its path. For each enemy that Powershot hits, its damage is reduced by 20%.
language.lore: During her early years of training, Lyralei learned to fire powerful arrows that cleaved even trees to reach their targets.
notes: Powershot will destroy trees in its area of effect.

description: Increases movement speed and adds evasion from all physical attacks, while slowing movement of nearby enemies.
language.lore: Lyralei enchants gusts of winds to fight incoming attacks.
language.aghanimDescription: Grants %max_charges% charges to Windrun, increases movement speed, and removes movement speed limit.
notes: Activating Windrun will evade incoming projectiles.

description: Windranger channels the wind to gain 475 additional attack speed against a single enemy unit or structure, though with a reduction to her attack damage. Extra damage from secondary item effects is not reduced.
language.lore: Lyralei's ability to bombard opponents with a flurry of arrows is unparalleled - even at the expense of accuracy.
notes: Issuing a Hold Position command will pause Windranger's attacks.
Windranger can move while attacking.

description: Blasts the target enemy unit with damaging frost, dealing area damage and slowing movement and attack rates for 4.0 seconds. The primary target receives both base and area damage.
language.lore: Frost-mage Ethreain has not forgotten even the simplest of ice manipulation.

description: Creates a shield around the target friendly unit or building, which adds armor and slows attacking units. Lasts 40.0 seconds.
language.lore: Originally crafted during his ambush for self-defense, the Lich is capable of enchanting others with a formidable defense of frost magic.
notes: If autocast is activated, Lich will cast this spell on nearby allies who are attacked.

description: Applies a magical frost shield around the target, reducing damage from attacks against you. While the shield is active, ice magic will affect nearby enemy units every 1 seconds, dealing minor damage and slowing them.
language.lore: First conceived of to protect him in his mortal years, the frost magic that Ethreain weaves around himself has only grown colder with time.
notes: Spell-immune enemies are not affected by the damage or slow.
Frost Shield can be cast on buildings.

description: Releases an orb of frost that bounces between nearby enemy units up to 10 / 10 / 10 times, slowing and damaging each time it hits. Each bounce increases the damage for the subsequent bounces.
language.lore: Almost universally considered the ultimate in frost magic, Ethreain's orb of frozen death strikes fear into those who dare stand against him.
notes: Chain Frost cannot be disjointed.
Chain Frost has a movement speed of 850.
Chain Frost doesn't bounce to Zombies.

description: Launches a cask of paralyzing powder that ricochets between enemy units, stunning and damaging those it hits.
language.lore: The Witch Doctor recycles the bones of fallen friends and foes, using the powder as part of his arsenal of charms and alchemy.
notes: Targets can be hit multiple times, as long as another unit is struck in between the bounces.

description: Witch Doctor focuses his magic to heal nearby allied units, costing Witch Doctor mana every second Voodoo restoration is active.
language.lore: Zharvakko's hocus pocus is not limited only to hexxing his opponents and is quite adept at curing ailments.
notes: Healing is done in 0.33 / 0.33 / 0.33 / 0.33 second intervals.
Can heal Spell Immune units.

description: Curses all enemy Heroes in a small area, causing them to take a set amount of damage each second, as well as bursts of damage every 4 seconds based on how much health they have lost since the curse began.
language.lore: Certain voodoo magics can make an enemy regret engaging the Witch Doctor.
notes: If an affected hero's health has increased above the amount they had when Maledict was cast, the burst damage will be 0.

description: CHANNELED - Summons a deadly ward to attack enemy heroes within it's attack range. Lasts a maximum of 8.0 seconds.
language.lore: Witch Doctor performs a ritualistic dance, one that haunts the dreams of those who live to recount it.
language.aghanimDescription: Death Ward attacks have True Strike and bounce between nearby enemies.
notes: The Death Ward is invulnerable, and is only destroyed if Witch Doctor is interrupted or its duration expires.
The Death Ward can be controlled, and made to attack a specific target.
Death Ward attacks once every 0.22 seconds.

description: Throws down a smoke bomb, silencing enemies, and causing them to miss attacks.
language.lore: Since his escape during the night of his betrayal, Riki has valued the use of a simple smoke screen to confuse his opponents.
notes: Doesn't prevent the use of active items.

description: Teleports behind the target unit, striking for bonus damage if it is an enemy.
language.lore: The Stealth Assassin's agile movement makes him impossible to escape.
notes: Riki's first attack after Blink Strike will be a backstab.
Blink Strike's damage is dealt before the next attack.
You can Blink Strike to allies, but no damage is dealt.

description: Riki fades into the shadows, becoming invisible. Every time Riki strikes his enemy from behind, he deals bonus damage based on his Agility. When Riki attacks, he becomes visible.
language.lore: Riki comes for you.
notes: Illusions of Riki will play Backstab animations, but not deal any bonus damage.
Bonus damage from Backstab can't be evaded.

description: Riki phases out of the world while striking random enemy units from behind in an area around him.
language.lore: The Stealth Assassin is not afraid to fight dirty, and specializes in attacking his opponents from behind.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases duration, attacks, cast range and allows you to target an allied hero, hiding inside them for the duration.
notes: Moving while phased out will cancel the ability.

description: Focuses Enigma's power on a target, causing it to take damage and become repeatedly stunned for multiple instances. An instance strikes every 2.0 / 2.0 / 2.0 / 2.0 seconds.
language.lore: Strange gravities pull at the core of those who would oppose you, holding them in place.

description: Transforms a creep into three fragments of Enigma himself.  These eidolons are all under Enigma's control, and repeated successful attacks cause them to multiply.  When this happens, the eidolons have their health restored.
language.lore: Enigma is capable of drawing aspects of himself from other dimensions - the result is a trio of dark eidolons that hunt the corporeal plane.
notes: Converted enemy units will give gold bounty and experience.
Converted allied units will be denied.

description: Steeps an area in dark resonance, damaging enemy units based on their max HP.
language.lore: A section of the world slowly descends into the void.
notes: Damage goes through spell immunity.
This ability destroys trees in its area.
Multiple instances of Midnight Pulse will stack.

description: CHANNELED - Summons a vortex that sucks in nearby enemy units.  Enemies affected by Black Hole cannot move, attack, or cast spells.
language.lore: The ground trembles as Enigma channels his ultimate vortex of destruction, a singularity with the power to end worlds.
language.aghanimDescription: Adds the current level of Midnight Pulse to Black Hole.
notes: Disables enemies through spell immunity.

description: Fires an intense energy beam, dealing damage and blinding the target, causing it to miss all physical attacks.
language.lore: Boush perfected this rock cutting laser in his subterranean laboratory, never considering its combat utility.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes Laser to refract between all visible enemy heroes within range.

description: Launches rockets at the nearest visible enemy heroes within 2500 / 2500 / 2500 / 2500 range.
language.lore: The last contraption Boush was able to save was a retrofitted rocket launcher with a homing mechanism.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases Heat-Seeking Missile target count.

description: Enlists an army of robotic minions to destroy enemy units in an area around Tinker.
language.lore: Even though the laboratory has since been sealed off, the ability to radio in robotic drones is still in working order.
notes: Robots spawn at a rate of 24 per second.

description: CHANNELED - Resets the cooldown on most of Tinker's items and abilities.
language.lore: A new battery here, another set of rockets there, Boush continually improves on existing technology.
notes: Rearm works on all items except Aeon Disk, Arcane Boots, Black King Bar, Hand of Midas, Helm of the Dominator, Linken's Sphere, Meteor Hammer, Necronomicon, Pipe of Insight, Tome of Knowledge, and Refresher Orb.

description: Consumes a charge to launch a ball of shrapnel that showers the target area in explosive pellets. Enemies are subject to damage and slowed movement. Reveals the targeted area. Shrapnel charges restore every 40 seconds.
language.lore: Kardel's modular rifle also fires incendiary rounds, useful for assaulting entrenched locations.
notes: Damage is dealt 11 times, immediately at spell effect then every second.
Does not damage buildings.
Provides vision in the targeted area.

description: Sniper increases his accuracy, giving him a chance to deal extra damage and briefly knocks back his enemies.
language.lore: Taking potshots at steepstalkers in his childhood has been thoroughly refined into perfect leads on enemy combatants.
notes: Works on allied creeps.

description: Extends the attack range of Sniper's rifle. Can be activated to double the attack range bonus for 1 attack. Goes on cooldown after the attack is used.
language.lore: Kardel always takes it upon himself to stay as far from harm as he can while still performing his role - taking perfect aim.

description: Sniper locks onto a target enemy unit and, after a short aiming duration, fires a devastating shot that deals damage at long range and mini-stuns the target.
language.lore: In order to fulfill the prophecy and return to his home town, Kardel must make another shot as perfect as the one on the day of his ancient test.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes Assassinate to fire quicker and disable the enemy target.
notes: Crosshair effect is only visible to allies.
Invisibility doesn't disjoint the projectile.
Interrupts channeling spells, including on Spell Immune units.

description: Necrophos releases a wave of death around him, dealing damage to enemy units and healing allied units.
language.lore: Poor souls who succumb to Rotund'jere's plagues are recycled for future use.
notes: Death Pulse can't be disjointed.
Can heal Spell Immune units.

description: Necrophos stills the hearts of his opponents, causing nearby enemy units to lose a percentage of their max health over time. Passively provides regen for 7 seconds for each unit Necrophos kills.
language.lore: Those who come within a short distance of Necrophos can feel pestilence and plague in the air.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases Heartstopper Aura damage while Ghost Shroud is active.
notes: Damage won't disable items like Blink Dagger.
Does not affect ancient creeps.

description: Necrophos slips into the realm that separates the living from the dead. Unable to attack or be attacked, he emits an aura that slows enemies around him. He takes additional magic damage in this form, but his restorative powers are amplified.
language.lore: Rotund'jere uses the souls of his victims as bridge from life to afterlife.
language.aghanimDescription: Reduces Ghost Shroud cooldown.

description: Stuns the target enemy hero, then deals damage based on how much life it is missing. Heroes killed by Reaper's Scythe will have 15 / 25 / 35 seconds added to their respawn timer. Any kill under this effect is credited to Necrophos.
language.lore: The amount of death and suffering in the air increases the power of Necrophos's plague magic.
notes: Damage is dealt at the end of the stun.

description: Binds several enemy units together, causing a percentage of the damage dealt to one of them to be felt by the others.
language.lore: An ancient incantation that links the vital energies of multiple lifeforms into one collective body.
notes: The shared damage type is the same as the type of damage inflicted.

description: Warlock whispers an incantation, healing a friendly unit or damaging an enemy unit over time.
language.lore: Demnok's arcane arts have a myriad of uses, allowing them to be powerful friendly enchantments or damaging curses.

description: CHANNELED - A powerful slowing current that grows stronger as it's channelled. Lasts up to 16.0 seconds. Enemies are slowed for 3.0 seconds after leaving the area or the spell ends.
language.lore: Demnok manipulates space-time, impairing entire armies.
notes: The slow increase is based on length of the channel, not the duration an enemy was standing in the area.

description: Summons a Golem from the depths, stunning enemies for one second. The Golem lives 60 / 60 / 60 seconds, takes reduced damage from spells, has Permanent Immolation and Flaming Fists on attack.
language.lore: Demnok unleashes the captive spirit in his Dreadwood staff, causing destruction in enemy ranks.
language.aghanimDescription: Calls %number_of_golems_scepter% Golems with reduced stats and bounty.
notes: Spell Immune units will be stunned.
This ability destroys trees in its area of effect.

description: Deals extra damage to nearby units when attacking.
Burns the Golem's nearby enemy units, with damage per second.

Beastmaster sends his axes flying and calls them home again, slicing through enemy units and trees along their path.  Each axe can hit an enemy once, and amplifies subsequent damage from Beastmaster and his units.
language.lore: While learning to maneuver in nature alone, the Beastmaster also mastered the use of a pair of tomahawks, adept at cutting down trees as well as adversaries.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes Wild Axes to have no cooldown, and can be used again once they come back.
notes: This ability destroys trees.

description: If motionless for some time, the hawk becomes invisible.
Inflicts a poison that slows attack and movement speeds.
Untaps the inner fury of nearby allies, passively increasing their attack speed.
language.lore: Beastmaster's ability to incite the innate strength of animals was seen in the mauling of the king of Slom.

description: Hurls a poisoned dagger which deals large initial damage, and then deals damage over time. The poisoned unit has its movement speed slowed for 15.0 seconds. An instance of damage is dealt every 3.0 seconds.
language.lore: Akasha's envenomed dagger allows her to delight in the drawn out suffering of her victims.
notes: The affected unit slowly regains its original movement speed every second during the duration.
Units afflicted by Shadow Strike can be denied by their allies when their HP drops below 25% of their maximum health.

description: Short distance teleportation that allows Queen of Pain to move in and out of combat.
language.lore: The Secret Queen lives up to her title, making her pain impossible to escape.
notes: You can use Blink to dodge incoming projectiles.

description: The Queen of Pain lets loose a piercing scream around her, damaging nearby enemies.
language.lore: The sultry voice of Akasha beckons her opponents while stealing their souls.
notes: Scream Of Pain will hit invisible units.
Scream Of Pain cannot be disjointed.

description: Creates a gigantic wave of sound in front of Queen of Pain, dealing heavy damage to all enemy units in its wake and pushing them back.
language.lore: Her most exquisite of all of torments, Akasha's Sonic Wave puts her poor foes out of their misery.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases damage and decreases cooldown.
notes: Sonic Wave can hit units up to 1150 units away.

description: Beastmaster lets loose a deafening roar that stuns, and shoves open a path to its target. All units in the path of the roar are damaged, while units shoved aside by the roar have their movement and attack speed slowed. Additionally, Beastmaster and his units gain 40% movement speed for 3 seconds.
language.lore: The Beastmaster has learned to channel his primal instincts into an animalistic roar, causing devastation in the ranks of enemies.

description: Launches a ball of venom in a line, poisoning enemy units so that they take both initial damage and damage over time, as well as suffering slowed movement.  Venomous Gale deals damage every 3 seconds over its duration.
language.lore: A concoction of various stings, poisons, and toxins gathered from the jungles of Jidi Isle, victims surviving it are rare.
notes: Venomous Gale can be lethal. Units afflicted by Venomous Gale can be denied when their HP drops below 25%.
Duration damage is dealt every 3.0 / 3.0 / 3.0 / 3.0 seconds.
Slow starts at -50 / -50 / -50 / -50%, and decreases as time passes.

description: Adds poison damage to Venomancer's normal attacks and slowing movement speed.
language.lore: The paralytic sting of the creature which caused his transformation now belongs to the Venomancer.
notes: Poison Sting damage can be lethal.
Damage from Poison Sting does not interrupt healing from items, nor does it activate the cooldown on Blink Dagger.

description: Summons a plague ward to attack enemy units and structures. The ward is immune to magic. Wards gain the Poison Sting level from Venomancer, dealing 50% of the full damage.
language.lore: A mixture of his old herbalist talents and newfound toxic mastery creates a living embodiment of plague.

description: A spreading ring of poison that does damage over time to enemy units around Venomancer.  Poison Nova cannot deal lethal damage; targets will be left with at least 1 health.
language.lore: In the Acid Jungles, creatures releasing noxious poison to their attackers is common; Venomancer spreads this plague beyond the Jidi Isle.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases damage and decreases cooldown.

description: Rushes to a target location while backtracking any damage taken the last 2.0 seconds.
language.lore: Darkterror tears a hole in time, passing through Claszureme, and appearing back in an instant.
language.aghanimDescription: Applies a Time Lock proc to all units at the landing destination.
notes: Faceless Void is invulnerable while using Time Walk.

description: Adds the chance for an attack to lock an enemy unit in time while attacking it a second time.
language.lore: The strike of the Faceless Void lands with dimension shifting force.
notes: Does not stack with Skull Basher.

description: Creates a blister in spacetime, trapping all units caught in its sphere of influence and causes you to move very quickly inside it.  Only Faceless Void and any units he controls are unaffected.  Invisible enemies in the sphere will be revealed.
language.lore: When a rift opens to Claszureme, all poor souls caught within will likely never return.
notes: Pauses all units and buildings, friendly or enemy, except those owned by Faceless Void.
Faceless Void is never affected by Chronospheres with any owner.

description: An exploding pulse deals damage to enemies and structures in the area.  Deals half damage to structures.
language.lore: The Arts of Oblivion include a deafening blast of emerald flames from the Nether Reaches.
notes: Damage is delayed by 0.9 / 0.9 / 0.9 / 0.9 seconds.

description: A powerful banishing spell that slows a unit and renders it unable to attack or be attacked. Afflicted units take extra magic damage.
language.lore: A now-mastered relic from his childhood, Pugna delights in banishing others into the Nether Realm, whether for good, evil, or simple enjoyment.
notes: Only magical and pure damage can affect a unit under the effects of Decrepify.
Doesn't slow allied units.
Can be used on your Nether Ward.

description: Pugna places a Nether Ward at the target location. The ward causes nearby enemy heroes to lose a percentage of their max mana every second, and will fire at any enemy hero who casts a spell. Nether Ward deals base damage plus the damage multiplier of the mana spent by the enemy hero.
language.lore: While at the lamasery for the Arts of Oblivion, Pugna learned to dominate his classmates with a simple ward charged with Nether magic.
notes: Nether Ward deals damage before the actual spell is cast, so if the caster dies the spell will have no effect.
Nether Ward can be decrepified.
Illusions and creeps deal 25% damage to Nether Ward.

description: CHANNELED - When cast on an enemy, Pugna drains health from the target enemy unit to heal himself and granting vision over the target. If Pugna has full HP, and the enemy target is a Hero, Life Drain will restore mana instead.
When cast on an ally, Pugna will drain his own health into his ally.
language.lore: Pugna has truly become more powerful than even the grandmaster of Oblivion.
language.aghanimDescription: Removes cooldown and increases damage.
notes: Health gained depends on the actual damage dealt.
Illusions are destroyed on the first tick of damage.

description: Throws a dagger slowing the enemy unit's movement speed, dealing 65+ 25 / 40 / 55 / 70% of Phantom Assassin's attack damage as physical damage and applying attack effects from items and abilities.
language.lore: The first skill learned by the Sisters of the Veil often signals an incoming hit.
notes: If an attack effect is chance-based, the chance of its application will be the same as its chance to occur.
Spell-immune enemies are not affected by Stifling Dagger's slow.

description: Teleports to a unit, friendly or enemy, and grants bonus attack speed while attacking if it's an enemy unit.
language.lore: Mortred's silken veil is the last thing her unfortunate target sees.

description: Phantom Assassin focuses inward, increasing her ability to evade enemy attacks. Can be activated to blur her body, causing her to be impossible to see until near enemy heroes.
Stacks diminishingly with other sources of Evasion.
language.lore: Meditation allows a Veiled Sister to carefully anticipate her opponents in combat.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes Blur to have instant cast time and applies a dispel. Anytime you get a hero kill, your abilities are refreshed. Reduces Blur cooldown.

description: Phantom Assassin refines her combat abilities, gaining a chance of delivering a devastating critical strike to enemy units. Stifling Dagger shares the same critical strike chance.
language.lore: A divine strike, Mortred honors her opponent by choosing them for death.

description: Templar Assassin becomes highly elusive, avoiding damage and gaining a bonus to her damage.  The damage and avoidance effects are separate, and have a limited number of instances.
language.lore: Manipulating her psionic veil, Lanaya bends nature's law to her will.
notes: Damage as HP Removal bypasses Refraction (it won't reduce the charges).
Only instances of 5 / 5 / 5 / 5 or more damage will trigger Refraction.
Refraction is visible to enemies.

description: Templar Assassin conceals herself, becoming invisible as long as she remains still. If Meld's invisibility is broken by attacking an enemy, Lanaya will deal bonus damage to the enemy and reduce their armor for 12 seconds.
language.lore: Lanaya is as elusive as her covenant with the Hidden Temple.
notes: Meld is broken by any action other than staying in position.
Meld's armor reduction does not work against towers.

description: Templar Assassin's psi blades slice through the attacked unit, splitting and damaging enemy units directly behind it, while gaining bonus attack range.
language.lore: Her blades pierce the skin as much as the mind, furthering her understanding of the mystery that is reality.
notes: Split damage hits invisible units.
Attack effects like Bash will only be applied to the main target.

description: Templar Assassin places mystical traps that invisibly monitor enemy movement. When sprung at her command, they exert a slowing influence of 30% in the area. Traps charge up to slow 60% after 4 seconds. Deals bonus damage when fully charged.
language.lore: Calling upon the reach of the Hidden Temple, none escape the eye of the Templar.
language.aghanimDescription: Grants new ability: Psionic Projection. Allows you to teleport to any Psionic Trap after a brief channel.
notes: Traps last indefinitely.
They have invisibility that fades in over 2.0 / 2.0 / 2.0 seconds, spell immunity, and 100 HP.
Traps have 400/400 vision range and don't prevent neutral camps from spawning.

description: Springs the nearest trap, slowing nearby enemies.
Springs the trap, slowing nearby enemies.
Deals damage to the unit that kills the Necronomicon Warrior.
Reveals invisible units.
Mana burned per hit, a portion of which is dealt as damage.
Launches an arrow that burns away the targeted unit's mana, dealing damage equal to the amount of mana burned.
Increases movement and attack speed of nearby units.
Returns the courier to base
Transfer items to hero
Return items to stash
Retrieve items from stash
Summons a protective shield around the courier
The courier gains a burst of speed for 6.0 seconds
Roshan will block one targeted spell every 15 seconds. Also reduces status effects by 25%.
Roshan has a chance to stun on attack.
Roshan slams the ground, damaging and slowing all nearby enemies. Slam's damage will increase every minute.
Roshan possesses numerous protective abilities, including 55% magic damage resistance, the ability to reduce damage from attacking illusions, and a scaling armor bonus that increases as time goes on.
Intensifies Viper's venom, adding an effect to his normal attack that applies a stacking movement speed slow and magic resistance deduction while dealing damage over time. Stacks up to 5 times.
language.lore: The Netherdrake's inborn toxic breath quickly drains the vitality of its afflicted.

description: Viper releases a Nethertoxin at the targeted area. Units in that area take an increasing damage over time based on how long they remain in it. Disables passives of affected units.
language.lore: Poison from the Nether Reaches turns wounds into fatalities, and fatigue into death.

description: Viper exudes an infectious toxin that damages and slows the attack speed of any enemy that damages it in a 1400 radius. The acid exudate also increases Viper's resistance to magic.
language.lore: It is not unusual for sword and shield alike to corrode in the very hands of those who attack the Netherdrake.
notes: Stacks multiplicatively with other magic damage resistance sources.

description: Viper slows the targeted enemy unit's movement and attack speed while also dealing poison damage over time.  The slowing effect reduces over the duration of the poison.
language.lore: Once used to slay his sadistic summoner, the most powerful of Netherdrake infections spreads through the veins of those foolish enough to cross Viper.
language.aghanimDescription: Decreases mana cost and cooldown, and increases cast range.

description: Calls a beam of lunar energy down upon an enemy, damaging and briefly stunning them.
language.lore: Selemene smites those who encroach upon the Nightsilver Woods.

description: Empowers Luna's glaives, causing her attacks to bounce between enemy units. Deals less damage with each bounce.
language.lore: Carefully sharpened, Luna's boomerang-like weapon cuts a wide swath through enemy numbers.
notes: Moon Glaives do not proc any attack modifier except Critical Strikes.

description: Increases the attack damage for Luna and nearby allied ranged player units. Luna is also blessed with increased vision range at night.
language.lore: The Goddess of the Moon smiles upon her kin.

description: Showers random nearby enemies with strikes from Luna's current level of Lucent Beam. These beams do not stun their targets, and there is a maximum number of times that a single target can be struck. Also turns day into night for 10.0 seconds.
language.lore: In times of great need, Selemene herself descends into the world, blocking out the light and hope of the opposed.
language.aghanimDescription: Allows Luna to cast Eclipse on an allied unit or herself and have its effects follow them, or cast it on an area. Also increases total beams and duration, removes the limit on beams per unit, and makes the beams appear twice as fast.
notes: Eclipse doesn't work if Luna doesn't have any points in Lucent Beam.
Beams will stop if Luna is killed.
Will not hit invisible units.
There is a 0.6 / 0.6 / 0.6 seconds gap between beams, 0.3 seconds with scepter.

description: Unleashes a breath of fire in front of Dragon Knight that burns enemies and reduces the damage their attacks deal.
language.lore: Knight Davion's breath has become that of the mighty Eldwurm Slyrak, remembered for burning numerous other knights to a crisp.
notes: Hits units up to 900 away.
