language.lore: A torrent from the Deep Ones crushes the defenses of the Siren's enemies.

description: All enemies in range of the Naga Siren are put into a magical stasis where they cannot act or be attacked. Using Song of the Siren again will end the duration early.
language.lore: Slithice's powerful voice enchants leagues of opponents, while calling her Slithereen kin in a time of need.
language.aghanimDescription: Song of the Siren regenerates all nearby allies for a percentage of their max health per second.
notes: Units affected by Song of the Siren are invulnerable and cannot take damage from any source.
Doesn't affect Spell Immune units.
The area of the song follows Naga, so if she moves far enough away from affected units, they will wake up.

description: Channels light energy, building power the longer it's channeled.  Once released, a wave is sent forth that deals damage and gives vision in its path.  The longer it is channeled, the more damage is dealt.
language.lore: Ezalor's hidden light reveals itself in marvelous fashion.
language.aghanimDescription: Allows Illuminate to heal allies during the day for the same amount as its damage values, and causes Illuminate to not require channeling.
notes: Gives increasing vision over the channeling time.

description: Weakens an enemy's magical essence, causing them to lose mana as they move.  If the enemy loses all of its mana, it will be stunned.
language.lore: Ezalor disrupts Primordial harmony, draining magical energy from those with poor constitution.
notes: If the target travels over 300 distance in less than 0.1 second (by using blink skills, for example), Mana Leak will not decrease its mana for that distance.

description: Restores mana to the target unit and reduces cooldowns of all abilities currently on cooldown by a fixed amount. Can be cast on enemy, placing a debuff that drains 4.5 / 5 / 5.5 / 6.0% of current mana per 100 units moved.
language.lore: In the same vein, Ezalor bestows his harmony among others.
notes: Chakra Magic does not reduce the cooldown of Ultimate abilities

description: Ezalor temporarily turns his body luminescent, gaining various abilities.  Illuminate is now channeled by a separate spirit, and gains the Blinding Light and Recall abilities.
language.lore: In a flash of light, Ezalor reveals his true nature.
language.aghanimDescription: Permanent Spirit Form. During daytime, allows Illuminate to heal allies for the same amount as its damage values.

description: After a short delay, teleports the targeted friendly hero to your location.  If the targeted friendly hero takes player based damage during this time, the ability is interrupted.
language.lore: Walk towards the light.
notes: If Keeper of the Light dies, the spell effect is interrupted.
Recall will interrupt channeling spells.
You can disable help to prevent Keeper from casting this spell on you.
Can be cast through the minimap, choosing the nearest friendly hero.

description: A blinding light flashes over the targeted area, knocking back and blinding the units in the area, causing them to miss some attacks. Knockback is 350 range over 0.4 seconds,
language.lore: The Primordial light turns the tides of battle in favor of Ezalor and his allies.
notes: Upon landing, units will destroy trees in a 150 radius.

description: Release the channel early.
Release enemy units from your song so they can be targeted again.

Channels light energy, building power the longer it's channeled.  Once released, a wave is sent forth that deals damage and gives vision in its path.  The longer it is channeled, the more damage is dealt.
language.lore: Ezalor's hidden light reveals itself in marvelous fashion.
notes: Gives increasing vision over the channeling time.

description: Visage drains the movement and attack speed of the targeted unit, gaining it for itself.
language.lore: The warmth of the sun is never felt in the dark cold of the Narrow Maze.
notes: The two buffs can be removed separately by purge.
The speed gained is independent of the speed lost on the target.
Familiars within 900 range of Visage will also receive bonuses from Grave Chill.

description: Visage gathers charges of soul essence each time nearby heroes take more than 100 damage. When the essence is released, it deals base damage as well as damage for each gathered soul charge.
language.lore: The collected souls of the dead reach out to bring another into their fold.
notes: Charges are only gained for damage greater than 2.0 and less than 3000.0 that is dealt by a player or Roshan. Self-damage or Soul Assumption damage isn't counted.
Soul Assumption cannot be disjointed.

description: Visage generates a layered barrier that protects him from damage.  If he receives damage from a player, one layer is removed, and takes time to recover.
language.lore: Visage's tough scales share equal properties of ghost and stone, making it nearly impervious to blade and magical assault.
notes: Each time Visage receives damage greater than the Minimum Damage that was not self-inflicted and was from a player owned source, a layer is removed.
Familiars within 1200 range of Visage will receive the current damage reduction from Gravekeeper's Cloak.

description: Conjures two blind Familiars to fight for Visage.  Familiars possess the Stone Form ability, that allows them to turn into stone, stunning enemies upon landing.  While in Stone Form, Familiars are invulnerable, and rapidly regenerate their health.  Familiars grant high bounty when killed.
language.lore: Guardians of the Narrow Maze, Necro'lic's Familiars stand watch over his domain.
language.aghanimDescription: Summons a bonus Familiar.
notes: Casting Summon Familiars will replace any existing Familiars.
Familiars within range of Visage will receive bonuses from Gravekeeper's Cloak and Grave Chill.

description: After a short delay, the Familiar turns into stone and smashes into the ground, stunning and damaging all targets in the area. The Familiar becomes invulnerable, and will regain its health very rapidly. After 6.0 seconds, the Familiar will automatically leave Stone Form.

Tethers Io to an allied unit, granting bonus movement speed to both. When Io restores health or mana, tethered units target gains a larger portion of that amount. The tether breaks when the allied unit moves too far away, or Io cancels the tether.
language.lore: The benevolent touch of Io brings strength from between the planes.
notes: If you try to tether a unit that is 700 distance or further away from Io, he will latch on and pull himself closer to the tethered unit (to a distance of 300).
The tethered unit will heal faster and will heal even if Io is at full health.
Io's movement speed matches the tethered unit's.

description: Summon five particle spirits that dance in a circle around Io. If a particle collides with an enemy hero, it explodes, damaging all enemy units in an area around it.  Creeps take minor damage from touching a particle spirit, but do not cause them to explode.  When its duration ends, any remaining Spirits explode.
language.lore: Io twists the particles of the universe with its unimaginable capabilities.
language.aghanimDescription: Spirits now passively spawn around you constantly every second. Max of 5.
notes: After summoning, Io can call the spirits in and out.

description: Io gains bonus attack speed and HP Regen based on max health.  If Io is Tethered to an ally, that unit also gains the bonuses.
language.lore: Drawing on the energy of matter from all worlds, Io begins the unravelling of time.

description: Teleports Io and any tethered ally to any location. After the spell expires Io and any tethered ally will return to their original location. Double-click to teleport to your team's base fountain.
language.lore: Io is the embodiment of the mystery of the universe.
notes: Enemies receive a visual indicator in the world and on the minimap of the target location during the cast delay.
If Io is disabled during the cast delay, Relocate is cancelled.
If an allied hero is Tethered, that hero will teleported along with you. You can break the tether at any time to prevent that hero from teleporting with you.

description: Break the link to the tethered unit.
Calls the spirits in and out.
Provides bonus mana regeneration to all nearby allies.
Sends the courier to your team's secret shop
Sends the spirits farther away from you. Can be toggled on and off.
After a short delay, Slark sacrifices some of his life blood, purging most negative debuffs and dealing damage to enemy units around him and to himself.  Slark only takes 50% of the damage.
DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
language.lore: Slithereen are capable of quickly regrowing appendages, in case of critical injury, to save their own lives.
notes: 1.5% seconds after cast, a series of 10 pulses separated by 0.1 seconds deal the damage.
Each pulse also removes debuffs from Slark.
You can't kill yourself with this skill.
The pulses stop if Slark dies.

description: Slark leaps forward, grabbing the first hero he connects with.  That unit is leashed, and can only move a limited distance away from Slark's landing position.
language.lore: Time in the Dark Reef made Slark a dangerous assassin; aggressive and fearless.
language.aghanimDescription: Provides %max_charges% charges and increases pounce range.
notes: On cast, Slark leaps forward at a speed of 933.33, stopping when he latches onto an enemy hero or has traveled 700 distance.
Spell Immune units cannot be leashed.
Trees will be destroyed around Slark's landing location.

description: Slark steals the life essence of enemy heroes with his attacks, draining each of their attributes and converting them to bonus Agility. If Slark kills an affected enemy hero, he permanently steals 1 Agility.
language.lore: With each strike at his adversaries, Slark's knowledge of their weaknesses improves.
notes: Attributes cannot be dropped below 1.
Essence Shifted stats are returned to normal on death. The stat return for Slark and for the affected hero are separate.
To permanently steal Agility, Slark doesn't need to land the killing blow, as long as the enemy hero is killed within 300 range of Slark while having the Essence Shift debuff.

description: When used, Slark hides himself in a cloud of shadows, becoming immune to detection. Attacking, casting spells, and using items will not reveal Slark.  Passively, when not visible to the enemy team, Slark gains bonus movement speed and health regeneration.
language.lore: The hidden Thirteenth is a slippery foe.
language.aghanimDescription: Reduces cooldown and causes Shadow Dance active to be an area of effect ability, hiding nearby allied heroes underneath it. Allies do not gain bonus movement speed or health regeneration.
notes: If Slark is damaged by a neutral unit, the passive movement and health regeneration bonuses are lost for 2.0 / 2.0 / 2.0 seconds.
The passive movement and health regeneration bonuses have a 0.5 / 0.5 / 0.5 second activation and deactivation delay.

description: Permanently invisible when not attacking.
Release the channel early.
Medusa magically splits her shot into several arrows. These arrows deal a lower percent of her normal damage.
The extra targets will not receive other attack effects (such as critical strike).
language.lore: All who encounter the cursed Gorgon will feel her rage.
notes: Secondary targets will be the closest enemy units excluding the primary target.
If illusions of Medusa are created while Split Shot is active, they will also have this ability.

description: A mystic snake made of energy jumps from target to target dealing damage. After it reaches its last target, it returns to Medusa to replenish her with mana. The snake deals more damage per jump and returns 11 / 14 / 17 / 20% mana based on the targets' total mana.
language.lore: The Gorgon's curse is her greatest strength.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes Mystic Snake to turn enemies hit into stone. Stone duration increases with each bounce of the Mystic Snake.
notes: Mystic Snake cannot be disjointed.

description: Creates a shield that absorbs 70% of incoming damage in exchange for Medusa's mana.
language.lore: While Medusa was not gifted with eternal life upon birth, her curse bestowed her with impressive defensive powers.
notes: Absorbs damage before any damage reduction takes place, meaning that armor will not reduce the amount of mana needed to absorb damage.

description: Any enemy units looking at Medusa will have their movement and attack speed slowed. If 2.0 seconds of total time is accumulated looking at Medusa while Stone Gaze is active, that unit will turn to stone. Petrified units are stunned, and take bonus physical damage.
language.lore: The beauty of Medusa is legendary.
notes: Regardless of when a unit receives the Stone Gaze buff while the ability is active on Medusa, it will still receive the full debuff duration.

description: While active, Troll Warlord swaps from using ranged to melee attacks. Melee attacks have a chance to ensnare, preventing the target from moving or using mobility spells. Berserker's Rage also grants additional movement speed, armor, and decreases base attack time.
Whirling Axes has different functionality while Berserker's Rage is active.
language.lore: Like his anger, Troll Warlord's supply of axes is infinite.
notes: Cooldowns of items that are different for ranged and melee units will be based on which form Troll Warlord was in when the item was used.

description: Troll hurls a fistful of five axes in a cone shape over 1000.0 range, slowing and damaging enemy units.
language.lore: Only axes fueled by hate whirl with such a deadly spin.
notes: Does not affect Roshan.

description: Troll hurls two axes around him in a close range area of effect, damaging enemy units and causing them to miss some attacks.
language.lore: Keep your enemies close.
notes: Does not affect Roshan.

description: With each continuous blow on the same target, Troll gains increased attack speed.  If Troll changes targets, the stacks drop to zero.
language.lore: If at first you don't succeed, strike, strike again.

description: Troll unleashes a powerful battle trance, that forces you to continuously attack the closest enemy unit within 900 range, prioritizing heroes. Damage does not kill you during this mode. Grants you bonus lifesteal, attack speed and movement speed. Applies a Basic Dispel.
language.lore: An adrenaline rush of pure hatred quickens your blades.
language.aghanimDescription: Reduces Battle Trance cooldown and allows it to be cast on allied or enemy heroes. Lasts half duration on enemies.
notes: Troll can still use his abilities while affected by Battle Trance.
Troll can still be killed with Axe's Culling Blade.

description: Slams the ground, stunning and damaging nearby enemy units.
language.lore: When the mighty hoof of the Warrunner touches soil, the tremors are felt far and wide.

description: Centaur strikes a mighty blow at melee range, damaging both himself and a small area around the target. Deals extra damage based on your strength. Centaur cannot die from Double Edge.
language.lore: In the spurs of combat, Bradwarden's vicious strikes sometimes cause self-inflicted collateral damage.
notes: Double Edge deals magic type damage to both the targets and himself.

description: Centaur counters all attacks, dealing damage back to the attacker. Returns a fixed amount plus a percentage of your strength. Deals half damage to towers.
language.lore: Bradwarden has no need to parry his opponent's attacks; his armor-like hide does it for him.
notes: Retaliate triggers when the attack hits.
Retaliate deals damage to towers.

description: Centaur leads all allies into a vicious charge causing them to move through units at max speed and stop any enemy units they trample. Trampled enemies take damage based on Centaur Warrunner's strength. Each enemy can be trampled once.
language.lore: The great belt of Omexe, which labels Bradwarden as the greatest warrior of his kind, incites his fellow gladiators to follow him into barbarous combat.
language.aghanimDescription: Heroes affected by Stampede take reduced damage, and are able to run through obstructions, including trees and up cliffs.

description: Magnus sends out a wave of force, damaging enemy units in a line, pulling them towards him and slowing them for 0.9 seconds.
language.lore: Mt. Joerlak was a somewhat unstable mass, and Magnus has learned to channel its reverberations.

description: Gives an allied unit bonus damage and cleave on attack. Magnus receives 2 times the bonus.
language.lore: With a deep bellow, Magnus displays his true power.
notes: The bonus damage is based only on base damage and damage from primary attributes.
Cleave damage goes through spell immunity.
Ranged units cannot Cleave.

description: Magnus rushes forward, goring enemy units on his massive tusk. Heroes hit on the way will be dragged to the destination, then damaged and affected by slowed movement and attack speed.
language.lore: Magnoceros horns are valuable in direct proportion to their danger to prospective merchants.
language.aghanimDescription: Lowers cooldown, cast point and manacost.
notes: Doesn't affect Spell Immune units.

description: Magnus changes properties of matter, sucking all nearby enemies in front of him and stunning them with a powerful slam and dealing damage.
language.lore: Magnus fights with the fury of the erupting Mt. Joerlak.

description: Teleports an allied unit back to the base.  Creeps are teleported instantly, while Heroes have a delay before teleporting. If cast on Chen, all units controlled by Chen through Holy Persuasion will be teleported to him after a delay.
Ends all ongoing Nightmares.

Timbersaw whirls extremely sharp edges, damaging enemies and destroying trees around him in an area.  If an enemy hero is affected, it loses some of its primary attribute for a short duration.  Whirling Death will deal bonus damage per tree destroyed.
language.lore: In the case that Rizzrack gets surrounded by the the vines and plants of his nightmares, he has an immediate chainsaw defense.

description: Timbersaw fires a chain that embeds itself in the first tree it hits, pulling him towards it.  Any enemy in the path takes damage.
language.lore: You never know when you might need to escape from malevolent saplings.

description: Each time Timbersaw is attacked, he gains increased health regen and armor.
language.lore: The saw-suit is equipped to react to the slightest touch with fortified defenses.

description: Fires your main saw blade at the target location where it will spin in place, dealing damage in an area around it. Enemies caught in the saw blade will move more slowly for every 5% of health missing. The blade deals damage and cuts down trees in its path when fired and retracted. While active the ability costs mana, and you lose the ability to attack.
language.lore: The ultimate in anti-flora weaponry.
language.aghanimDescription: Grants a second Chakram.
notes: The Chakram will return if Timbersaw runs out of mana or moves over 2000.0 distance away.

description: Returns the Chakram to Timbersaw.
Covers a target in snot, causing it to have reduced armor and movement speed.  Multiple casts stack and refresh the duration.
language.lore: Having caught a cold while stuck in the snow, Bristleback turns it to his advantage.
language.aghanimDescription: Viscous Nasal Goo becomes a no target area of effect ability, applying to all enemies within range.

description: Sprays enemy units with quills dealing damage in an area of effect around Bristleback. Deals bonus damage for every time a unit was hit by Quill Spray in the last 14.0 seconds.
language.lore: An enforcer's honor can be a prickly thing.  So can his quills.
notes: Quill Spray damage is not reduced by damage block abilities.

description: Bristleback takes less damage if hit on the sides or rear. If Bristleback takes 210 damage from the rear, he releases a Quill Spray of the current level.
language.lore: Turning his back to a fight might be just the thing.
notes: Bristleback's rear is considered to be within 70 degrees from the back.
Bristleback's side is considered to be within 110 degrees from the back.

description: Bristleback works himself up into a fury every time he casts a spell, increasing his movement speed and damage.
language.lore: 'Temper, temper,' his mum always chided.  But in a fight, a temper can come in handy.
notes: Bristleback's illusions will receive the bonuses.
Items will not trigger Warpath.

description: Tusk compresses shards of ice into a ball of frozen energy that damages all enemies it comes in contact with. When the ball reaches its target destination the shards are released, creating a barrier that lasts for 4 / 5 / 6 / 7 seconds.
language.lore: In the frozen tundra near the Barrier, after the last sun of autumn has set, ice can form with alarming speed.
notes: Creates an impassable barrier.

description: Tusk begins rolling into a snowball. Allies within a 350 radius can also be added to the snowball by right-clicking on them, even while the snowball is moving. Once launched, any enemies caught in the snowball's path will be stunned and take damage. Each allied Hero in the snowball will add to its damage.
language.lore: Tales are still told of the wild feat that ended the grand brawl at White Fields.
notes: The snowball will break apart a maximum of 3 seconds after launch.
The snowball can be launched early by pressing using the Launch Snowball ability.
Doesn't carry illusions, but will carry Meepo clones and other units that Tusk controls.
Each Meepo clone added to the snowball will add its own bonus damage and speed.
Allies can click on a snowball to add themselves to it.

description: Tusk summons a Frozen Sigil by calling upon the deepest cold of winter. The Sigil creates a snowstorm which slows all enemy units within 600 range.
language.lore: The chill of home!
notes: If no order is given, the Sigil will follow Tusk.

The Sigil has unobstructed movement, has a 310 movement speed, requires 3/3/4/4 hero attacks to destroy and 12/12/16/16 creep attacks to destroy, provides 400/400 vision, and gives a 90/100/110/120 gold bounty.
Heroes deal 1 damage to the sigil, while non-hero units deal 0.25 damage.

description: Tusk connects with his mighty Walrus Punch, a critical strike so powerful it launches its victim into the air. The victim is slowed upon landing.
language.lore: It never matters who throws the first punch, only who throws the last.
language.aghanimDescription: Adds new ability: Walrus Kick. Kicks the target unit back, damaging them and slowing their movement speed.
notes: Walrus PUNCH has true strike.

description: Skywrath Mage launches a slow-moving bolt of arcane magic, dealing damage to an enemy unit based on Skywrath Mage's intelligence.
language.lore: Within the Ghastly Eyrie's endless intrigue, only the clever and calm can hope to survive.
language.aghanimDescription: When Skywrath Mage casts Arcane Bolt, a different random target within %scepter_radius% range willl be hit with the same ability. Heroes will take priority.
notes: The projectile moves very slowly (500 ms), providing 325 vision around it.  Upon impact, it will reveal the target area for 3.34 seconds.
Arcane Bolt cannot be disjointed.

description: Skywrath Mage sets off a long range shot that hits the closest hero within a long range.  Upon impact, it deals damage and slows in an area of effect.
language.lore: Those who serve the court of the Ghastly Eyrie are ever locked in covert war. One must always know where danger lurks nearest.
language.aghanimDescription: When Skywrath Mage casts Concussive Shot, a different random target within cast range will be hit with the same ability. Heroes will take priority.
notes: If no enemy heroes are in range or they are in fog, Concussive Shot targets the nearest enemy creep.
Damages creeps around the impact area.
Provides 400 vision around the projectile, and reveals the target area for 3.34 seconds upon impact.

description: Skywrath Mage seals the targeted unit with an ancient rune, silencing it and causing it to take additional damage from spells.
language.lore: A holy incantation, whosoever finds themselves touched by Avilliva's sigil must suffer in penitent silence.
language.aghanimDescription: Anytime Skywrath Mage casts Ancient Seal, a different random target within %scepter_radius% range will be affected by the same ability. Heroes will take priority.
notes: The magic damage resistance reduction doesn't affect creeps.

description: Skywrath Mage uses his ultimate magical ability to conjure a precise and violent mystical field that lays waste to his adversaries. Deals massive damage distributed evenly among any Heroes in the area over 2.4 seconds.
language.lore: Only the most practiced of Skywrath sorcerers could hope to shape the skies into such a storm.
language.aghanimDescription: When Skywrath Mage casts Mystic Flare, another Mystic Flare will be created on the position of a different random target enemy within %scepter_radius% range. Heroes will take priority
notes: Mystic Flare only affects Heroes; it does not damage illusions or creep heroes.
Spell immune enemies do not count toward the damage distribution.
Mystic Flare will damage enemy creeps if no enemy heroes are present.

description: Abaddon releases a coil of deathly mist that can damage an enemy unit or heal a friendly unit at the cost of some of Abaddon's health.
language.lore: A mysterious vapor from the Font of Avernus now infuses the breath of Abaddon, who releases it at will.
notes: Abaddon can not kill himself with this skill.

description: Summons dark energies around an ally unit, creating a shield that absorbs a set amount of damage before expiring. When the shield is destroyed it will burst and deal damage equal to the amount it could absorb to an area around it. Removes certain types of negative buffs and stuns on cast.
DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
language.lore: The powers of the black mist rise to absorb attacks like the black mist absorbs light.
notes: The max damage is always dealt whether the shield is destroyed by expiring or absorbing damage.
The explosion does not damage units hidden by the fog of war.

description: Abaddon strikes an enemy, slowing the target's movement speed. If the target gets hit 4 times, they become affected by a chilling curse causing them to be silenced and slowed, and all attacks against them gain an attack speed boost.
language.lore: While the baptized draw strength from the Font, the gifts of Avernus are debilitating to the uninitiated.

description: When activated, all damage dealt to you will heal instead of harm. Most negative buffs will also be removed. If the ability is not on cooldown, it will automatically activate if your health falls below 400.
DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
language.lore: The most unnatural of all the gifts of the Font of Avernus, this power defies mortal understanding.  What should hurt, instead heals; and what should kill gives strength anew.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases duration. While Borrowed Time is active, anytime an ally takes more than %ally_threshold_scepter% damage while within %redirect_range_scepter% range of Abaddon, an individual Mist Coil will automatically fire towards that ally.
notes: Borrowed Time can be manually activated while Abaddon is disabled, but not while silenced.  The passive activation can still occur while silenced.
Aphotic Shield does not block any damage to Abaddon when Borrowed Time is active, allowing him to heal.

description: Elder Titan and his Astral Spirit both stomp the ground, damaging and knocking nearby enemy units unconscious around their locations.  The Elder Titan stomp deals physical damage, while the Spirit stomp deals magical damage.
language.lore: The force of creation still echoes in the stomp of the Titan.
notes: If a unit is hit by Astral Spirit and Elder Titan, they will take both instances of damage.

description: Elder Titan and his Astral Spirit both stomp the ground, damaging and knocking nearby enemy units unconscious around their locations.  The Elder Titan stomp deals physical damage, while the Spirit stomp deals magical damage.  Unconscious enemies will wake if they take damage.
language.lore: The force of creation still echoes in the stomp of the Titan.

description: Elder Titan sends forth his Astral Spirit, damaging any units it passes through.  When the spirit rejoins the Titan, it grants bonus damage and movement speed for each unit it passed through.
The Astral Spirit can be controlled and possesses the Echo Stomp, Return Spirit, and Natural Order abilities.
language.lore: Like the four fundamentals, Elder Titan exists across all planes at once and can draw other aspects of himself to assist in times of need.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes you to become Spell Immune for %scepter_magic_immune_per_hero% seconds per affected enemy hero when the spirit returns to you.

description: Returns the Astral Spirit to Elder Titan.

Reduces all elements to their basic levels, removing base armor and magic damage resistance from nearby enemy units. The armor reduction is centered around the hero, while the magic armor reduction is centered around Astral Spirit.
language.lore: As it was at the beginning, Elder Titan makes it so again.
notes: When the Astral Spirit isn't present, both the armor and magic armor reduction is centered around Elder Titan.

description: Sends forth a jagged crack in front of Elder Titan. After 3 seconds, the crack implodes, slowing movement while dealing damage to each enemy based on their maximum life. Half of the damage dealt is Magical damage, while the other half is Physical damage.
language.lore: That which he created, the titan tears asunder.

description: Turns the enemies' numbers against them, dealing damage and granting you bonus movement speed per unit or per hero.  Deals bonus damage to illusions and summoned units as a percent of their current health.
language.lore: The archers of Stonehall are ready at Tresdin's command.

description: Removes debuffs and disables from the target friendly unit, and grants bonus attack speed and health regen for a short time.
DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
language.lore: The rallying horn of the Bronze Legion is able to inspire any heart.

description: When attacked, Legion Commander has a chance to immediately counterattack with bonus lifesteal.
language.lore: Tresdin knows that an enemy's most vulnerable moment often follows their fiercest stroke.

description: Legion Commander and the target enemy hero are forced to attack each other for a short duration.  Neither hero can use items or abilities.  If either hero dies during the duration, the hero winning the Duel gains permanent bonus damage.
language.lore: To face a soldier of Stonehall in single combat is a challenge few can resist.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases Duel duration, makes Legion Commander Spell Immune in Duel, and makes Legion Commander and her opponent only take damage from each other.
notes: Duels will end if the units are pushed 2000 units apart.
Winning a Duel automatically casts Press the Attack on yourself.

description: Plant an invisible mine that cannot be detected by True Sight, but is visible if an enemy is within the active 400 AoE of the mine. Mines detonate if an enemy is standing within the active AoE for 1.6 seconds. The explosion deals full damage in the blast radius, and deals 25% damage to buildings.
language.lore: The bane of Toterin!
language.aghanimDescription: Increases cast range.
notes: Cannot be placed within active AoE of another Proximity Mine.
Proximity Mines do not block neutral creep camps from spawning.
Mines last until they explode or are destroyed.
Mines are triggered by invisible units.
Mines will not be triggered by some flying units.
Grants 30 gold if destroyed by an enemy hero.
Mines are triggered by, but do not damage spell-immune units.

description: Plant an invisible trap that roots nearby enemy units instantly when triggered.
language.lore: The scourge of Trapper Town!
language.aghanimDescription: Increases cast range.
notes: Stasis Traps destroy all other Stasis Traps in their area of effect when they detonate.
Stasis Traps are not triggered by invisible units.
Stasis Traps do not block neutral creep camps from spawning.

description: Techies hurtle themselves into the enemy's midst, detonating charges upon impact which deal massive area of effect damage and silence enemies. Upon landing, the assault deals Techies damage equal to 50% of their max health.
language.lore: Where we going?
notes: Dying from this ability counts as suicide, and does not award gold or experience to the enemy team.
Techies still earn experience for suicide kills made with this ability.
This ability destroys trees.

description: Plant an invisible explosive that will only detonate after a brief delay when triggered.  Does not damage buildings.
language.lore: The downfall of Dredger's Bight!
language.aghanimDescription: Increases damage and cast range.
notes: Grants 10 gold if destroyed by an enemy hero.

description: Ember Spirit unleashes fiery bolas that wrap around nearby enemies, anchoring them in place and dealing damage each second.
language.lore: Xin's harshest lessons often employed the use of red-hot chains.
notes: Targets are chosen randomly around Xin.
Does not affect Spell Immune or invisible units.
Interrupts channeling spells.

description: Ember Spirit dashes around with blazing speed, attacking all enemies in the targeted area of effect, then returning to his start location.  Deals bonus damage to heroes, and less damage to creeps.
language.lore: The studied warrior must whip and weave through its enemies, burning each without pause.
notes: Targets are determined when the spell is cast.
A regular attack is done to each target every 0.2 seconds.
Any attack modifier that Xin has (such as Critical Strike, Bash, Cleave, or Orb effects) will be applied normally on these attacks.
Abilities and items can be used while Sleight of Fist is active.

description: Ember Spirit surrounds himself with a ring of fire that consumes incoming magic damage, leaving him unharmed.  Flame Guard deals damage per second in an area around Ember Spirit while Flame Guard is active.  If the shield is broken, the damage is also lost.
language.lore: An enemy should never be allowed to approach without difficulty.
notes: Magic damage reduction is calculated before any reductions.

description: Ember Spirit generates Fire Remnant charges every %charge_restore_time% seconds, with a max of %max_charges% charges. Releasing a charge sends a Fire Remnant that runs to the target location at 250% Ember Spirit's speed. Using Activate Fire Remnant, Ember Spirit can dash out to his Remnants, dealing damage along the way and exploding them upon arrival. The targeted Remnant will be arrived at last.
language.lore: By the spirit's power are Xin's teachings spread anew.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases cast range, initial remnant speed, and maximum charges. Activate Fire Remnant costs less mana.
notes: Starts with 3 charges (maximum).

description: Select the Fire Remnant to arrive at.
language.lore: With blazing speed does a spirit fly!

description: Earth Spirit smashes the target enemy or ally, sending them in the direction he is facing. If Earth Spirit targets an area, he will smash the nearest Stone Remnant in a 200 radius. The travelling unit or Remnant damages all enemy units it hits. If an enemy is hit by a Stone Remnant, they are also slowed. Stone Remnants travel further than other units.
language.lore: It is with the power of a mountain that Earth Spirit strikes his enemies.

description: Earth Spirit gathers himself into a boulder and, after a 0.6s delay, rolls toward the target location, damaging and stunning enemy units. He will stop if he collides with an enemy hero or is stunned. If he rolls over a Stone Remnant, he will travel further and faster, and stun enemies for longer.
language.lore: Calling upon his connection to the land, the Earth Spirit draws loose stone to him, which forms a protective ball that he can use to roll short distances.
notes: Rolling over a Stone Remnant will destroy the Remnant.
The boulder has a radius of 150.

description: Earth Spirit pulls the target Stone Remnant. Enemies struck by the gripped target will be silenced and take damage.
language.lore: Like calls to like. Even the minerals found in the blood and bones of living beings are not immune to the call of the Earth Spirit.
notes: Will not work on a unit inside Chronosphere, Duel, or Black Hole.
Geomagnetic Grip can also target allied creeps.

description: Call a Stone Remnant to the target location.  Stone Remnants have no vision and are invulnerable, and can be used with Earth Spirit's abilities.  Calling a Stone Remnant consumes a charge, which recharge over time.
language.lore: Earth Spirit calls forth a remnant of his stone army, long buried with him in the dark embrace of the Earth.
language.aghanimDescription: Grants a new ability: Enchant Remnant.

description: Magnetizes units in a small nearby area, causing them to take damage for a short duration. Magnetized heroes cause nearby Stone Remnants to explode, destroying the remnant and refreshing Magnetize's duration on all nearby enemies. This process can repeat multiple times. If an enemy hero is affected by Geomagnetic Grip or Boulder Smash, all magnetized heroes share the effects.
language.lore: At the Earth Spirit's call, the minerals in the blood and bones of his enemies rebel against the bodies they find themselves in.

description: Calls down waves of fire that damage enemy units in the target area, burning for additional damage over time.
language.lore: The flames of conquest blaze forth from the darkest depths of the abyss.

description: A deadly pit is conjured at the target location; any unit that enters will be rooted. Each enemy unit within the pit are affected every 3.6 seconds.
language.lore: Twisting into the seams of reality itself, Vrogros' manifest hatred paralyzes those who defy his will.

description: Nearby enemy units are weakened, losing a portion of their base damage. If an enemy dies while under this effect, Underlord gains temporary bonus damage.
language.lore: To merely stand in the presence of the Underlord is to feel the conviction of battle sapped from one's soul.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes bonus damage to be granted to nearby allied heroes within %radius% range for half the values.

description: Opens a dark rift at the targeted friendly unit's or building's position.  After a short delay, Underlord and all nearby friendly heroes are teleported to that unit's location.  Dark Rift can be cancelled at anytime during the cast.  If it is cancelled in this way or the target unit dies before the spell becomes active, Dark Rift goes into cooldown.
language.lore: They come without warning, leaving fire and blood where kingdoms once flourished.
notes: Double-click to teleport to your team's base fountain.

description: Stop the teleport.
Terrorblade brings forth an invulnerable dark reflection of all enemy heroes in a target area. Affected enemy heroes are slowed and attacked by their reflection.
language.lore: In the fractal prison of Foulfell, Terrorblade learned the truth of this old tale: you are your own worst enemy.  Now it is a lesson he teaches others.
notes: Reflections are untargetable, invulnerable illusions, that will be destroyed if the slow debuff is removed.
Reflections can only attack their source.

description: Creates an illusion of Terrorblade that deals damage.
language.lore: There's only one thing more dangerous than facing Terrorblade.  Facing MORE Terrorblades!
notes: Illusions created by Conjure Image are visually different for enemies.

description: Terrorblade transforms into a powerful demon with a ranged attack. Any of Terrorblade's illusions that are within 1200 range will also be transformed by Metamorphosis.
language.lore: Temper, temper. The rage rises up and takes control.  Meet Terrorblade's own worst self.
language.aghanimDescription: Grants you Terror Wave. Causes a wave to travel outwards in all directions forcing enemy heroes to become feared upon impact.
notes: Cooldowns of items that are different for ranged and melee units will be based on which form Terrorblade was in when the item was used.

description: Severs the life from both Terrorblade and a target hero, exchanging a percentage of both units' current health. Some health points must remain.
language.lore: You didn't need that life, did you?  The demon marauder steals that which you hold most dear.

description: Phoenix dives forward in an arc with a fixed distance in the targeted direction, dealing damage over time and slowing the movement speed of any units it comes into contact with, and then orbiting back to its original position. If Phoenix casts Supernova, the dive ends.
language.lore: Though no stranger to travelling the cosmic void, soaring within an atmosphere offers unique pleasures.
notes: Icarus Dive has a 2.0 second travel duration, and can be cancelled by casting the ability again while in flight.

description: Immediately cancels the dive.
language.lore: SCREE!

description: Summons 4 fire spirits that circle around Phoenix. Each spirit can be launched independently at a targeted area of effect. Affected enemy units take damage over time and have their attack speed greatly reduced.
language.lore: The ever-collapsing core of Phoenix often emits short-lived bursts of conscious light.
notes: Fire Spirits reveal the area they strike for 1 second.

description: Phoenix expels a beam of light at the cost of its own health. The beam damages enemies and heals allies for a base amount plus a percentage of their health. The percentage increases as the beam continues to fire.
language.lore: The vent through which such stellar energy flows is mere atoms wide.
notes: Sun Ray has a width of 130 units, and a length of %abilitycastrange% units.
Sun Ray is canceled if Phoenix gets stunned, silenced, cycloned, hexed or slept.
Phoenix can use items and abilities without canceling Sun Ray.

description: Immediately stops the Sun Ray.
language.lore: CHIRP!

description: Toggles slow forward movement during Sun Ray firing.
language.lore: SQAWRK!
notes: Sun Ray allows Phoenix to move over cliffs and trees.

description: The Phoenix willingly ends its current life for the chance to be reborn. Transforms into a burning sun that scorches enemies in a huge area. The sun can be destroyed by attacks from enemy Heroes. After 6.0 seconds the sun explodes, stunning all nearby enemies while restoring Phoenix to full health and mana with refreshed abilities.
DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
language.lore: The solar crucible of a Supernova may be fatal, yet from its flames arise new beacons to wander infinity.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases number of attacks to destroy Supernova and allows Phoenix to cast Supernova on an allied hero, bringing both into the sun to be reborn together.

description: Each fire spirit can be launched independently at a targeted area of effect. Affected enemy units take damage over time and have their attack speed greatly reduced.
language.lore: PKAWW! BOOM
notes: Fire Spirits reveal the area they strike for 1 second.

description: Releases a wave that silences and knocks back enemy units. Knockback distance is relative to how close they are to you.
language.lore: Traxex is rather fond of the tranquility of physical combat, calling on her Drow heritage to end the incantations of opposing magi.

description: Detonate all remote mines in the target area.
language.lore: Why light one fuse when you can light them all?

description: Detonate all selected remote mines.
language.lore: Kablooey!

description: CHANNELED - Gathers Oracle's power into a bolt of scouring energy that, when released, damages, roots, and purges enemies of buffs in an area around the target. If target is an ally it will only purge debuffs. The root duration is equal to the time spent channeling.
DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
language.lore: The astral orb crackles with power while raw energy lances out, temporarily disrupting an enemy's connection to their own body.
language.aghanimDescription: Increases cast range and stuns for a percentage of the duration.

description: Oracle enraptures a target, disarming them and granting them 100% magic damage resistance. Can be cast on allies and enemies.
language.lore: An unbreakable prophecy resounds: a chosen ally shall briefly suffer no magics.  Other kinds of suffering however...

description: Burns away impurities, dealing heavy magic damage to the target before causing them to regenerate health over time. The amount of health regenerated over its duration exceeds the amount of initial damage. Can be cast on enemies and allies.
language.lore: Like a hall of mirrors might amplify the light of a single candle, the shattered walls of the universe can transform the light of prophecy into a burning torch.
notes: The healing from Purifying Flames can be stacked with itself.

description: Temporarily alters an ally's destiny, delaying any healing or damage taken until False Promise ends. Any healing that is delayed by False Promise is doubled. Removes most negative status effects and disables on initial cast.
DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
language.lore: Foes and false prophets oft make lies of men's fates.
notes: Delayed damage and healing will take armor and magic resistance reductions into account when received.
The delayed damage and healing takes effect as soon as the target becomes vulnerable.

description: Launch the snowball toward the target.
language.lore: Into the great wide white!
notes: The snowball destroys trees.
Doesn't carry illusions, but will carry Meepo clones and other units that Tusk controls.
Each Meepo clone added to the snowball will add its own bonus damage and speed.

description: Destroys the selected Spin Web.
Plant a warning sign to remind enemies to step lightly. Only one sign can exist at a time. Lasts 180 seconds.
language.lore: Watch your step!
language.aghanimDescription: Allows Minefield Sign to hide any Proximity Mines, Stasis Traps, and Remote Mines in an area around the sign from True Sight.

description: Fires a secondary saw blade at the target location where it will spin in place, dealing damage in an area around it.  Additionally, for each 5% of health missing, enemies caught in the saw blade move more slowly. The blade deals damage and cuts down trees in its path when fired and retracted.  While active the ability costs mana, and you lose the ability to attack.
language.lore: Cut cut cut cut cut cut cut cut cut cut cut!
notes: The Chakram will return if Timbersaw runs out of mana or moves over 2000.0 distance away.
Slow effects from two chakrams do not stack.

description: Returns the Chakram to Timbersaw.
Earth Spirit temporarily enchants a hero, granting them the properties of a Stone Remnant. After a short duration the remnant shatters, releasing the hero and damaging nearby enemies.
language.lore: Kaolin uses the elemental power of the Earth to temporarily petrify living beings, so that they might be conscripted into his stone funerary army.

description: Treant Protector enchants a tree, which grants him unobstructed vision in that location. If Overgrowth is cast, units within a radius of an enchanted tree will be entangled and damaged.
language.lore: One can never be too certain who, or what, might need protecting.
notes: Being entangled by Overgrowth through enchanted trees from Eyes of the Forest does damage.
If the enemy has True Sight, they will be able to see which trees are enchanted.

description: Winter Wyvern soars upon an arctic wind, granting her unobstructed movement and allowing her to exhale a blistering chill into each attack. While soaring, her attacks travel further and faster, and slow enemies with a magical freeze that strips them of 6 / 7 / 8 / 9% of their current health each second. Her sight is also hardened against night's chill, granting her 400 additional vision range at night while soaring.
language.lore: The same organ where some dragons stoke their inner flame is, in Auroth, a crucible of unimaginable cold. From deep within her frosty gullet, an exhalation sends enemies into burning agony.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes Arctic Burn to be a toggle ability, draining mana every second when active. Removes limit on number of attacks per target.
notes: Enemy units can only receive the Arctic Burn debuff once per cast.
This ability does not affect Roshan.
Reduces Winter Wyvern's attack point to 0.1.
The damage and slow from Arctic Burn can be dispelled.

description: Launches a ball of brittle ice toward an enemy. The ice shatters on impact, leaving the primary target completely unaffected, while hurling damaging splinters into nearby enemies in a 500 radius. Enemies struck by these splinters are slowed by 30%.
language.lore: Produced slowly by specialized vesicles in her frozen gullet, Winter Wyvern blast shards of ice at her enemies.
notes: The primary projectile moves at 650 movement speed, or reaches the target in 1.0 second, whichever is faster.
The primary projectile cannot be disjointed.

description: Encases an ally in an icy cocoon, freezing them solid while healing a base amount as well as a percentage of their maximum health each second. The cocoon blocks all physical damage.
language.lore: From winter's heart comes a cold, healing embrace. The ice slows the blood and allows the spell to better work its curative magic.

description: Winter Wyvern freezes an enemy in place while striking those nearby with a maddening curse which causes them to attack their frozen ally with increased attack speed. The frozen ally and those cursed to attack their ally are immune to all damage from their enemies with the exception of Winter Wyvern or her controlled units.
language.lore: The oldest of the bookwurm’s spells, this curse lends truth to the old saw: sometimes the enemy of my enemy is my enemy still.
notes: If the target dies to its allies, Winter Wyvern will receive credit for the kill.
Will only pierce the spell immunity of the primary target, not the target's surrounding allies.

description: Lifestealer seizes control of the host body's nervous system, allowing him to issue movement and attack orders from within.  Controlled units share Lifestealer's movement speed.  Cannot be used on heroes.
Increases the health capacity of nearby units.

Nyx Assassin buries himself beneath the battlefield over a short duration. Once burrowed, Spiked Carapace instantly stuns nearby enemies when cast, the range of Mana Burn and Impale is increased, and Impale's cooldown is decreased. While burrowed, Nyx Assassin is stationary, unable to attack, and invisible. His health and mana regeneration are also increased, and he gains damage reduction from all damage sources.
language.lore: Some castes of zealot scarab are known to create small burrows to lie in wait, ready to ambush their prey.
notes: Casting Vendetta will cancel burrow.

description: On death, Mud Golems shatter into 2 Shard Golems. Shard Golems have 240 health, deal 9 damage per attack, and live for 60 seconds.
Stop.
Hurls a boulder at the target, damaging and stunning them. Golems do not do this unless commanded to.
language.lore: \"Why do they hesitate? What are they afraid of throwing?\"

description: Lifestealer swallows an allied hero, allowing them to hide within him. Any healing Lifestealer receives is shared with the hero within. When an assimilated hero leaves Lifestealer, they erupt outward, damaging nearby enemies.
DISPEL TYPE: Strong Dispel
language.lore: How can Lifestealer resist the chance to sample an ally?

description: Kicks the target unit back, damaging them and slowing their movement speed.
language.lore: Tusk may have made his name with his fists, but the wise enemy is wary of any and all limbs.

description: Emerge from the burrow.
language.lore: Some castes of zealot scarab are known to create small burrows to lie in wait, ready to ambush their prey.

description: Morphling creates a hybrid replication of a target allied hero, which can cast all of that hero's current, non-ultimate abilities. Enemies are able to see which unit is a hybrid.
Ejects an Assimilated hero, damaging nearby enemies.
Infuses a lone enemy unit with swirling, volatile energy, slowing its movement speed and dealing damage over time. The effect is muted if another enemy unit is near the target.
language.lore: An infinitesimal fraction of the power which imprisoned the Ancients.

description: Generates a circular distortion field of magnetic energy that protects allied heroes and buildings within it by evading attacks coming from outside the field.
language.lore: Time and space are of little consequence to one as old as Zet.

description: Summons a Spark Wraith that slowly materializes and patrols a targeted area until an enemy comes within its range. Once a target has been found the wraith fuses with them, dealing magical damage and slowing the unit.
language.lore: Lesser fragments of Zet's original self.
notes: Spark Wraiths can not be disjointed.

description: The Ancient Black Dragon's dreaded presence grants nearby allies additional armor. This bonus can stack with itself.
The rhythm of the Thunderhide's heartbeat increases the attack speed and accuracy of nearby allies.

Briefly refocusing its fractured elements into a single form, the Arc Warden is able to create a perfect electrical duplication of itself. The duplicate can use all of Arc Warden's current items and spells, except most consumables and items that drop on death. The duplicate has separate item and ability cooldowns.  The Tempest Double gives bounty gold to enemies when killed.
language.lore: Warped by the power of its peers, Arc Warden becomes what it despises most: disharmony.
language.aghanimDescription: Grants a new ability, Rune Forge. Creates a random Rune in front of you.
notes: Tempest Double and Refresher Orb cannot be used by the duplicate.

description: Passively grants you a chance to restore a percentage of your max mana each time you cast an ability. When activated, causes all abilities to slow enemies when they deal damage.
language.lore: The Outworld is awash in arcane energy, inclined to diffuse through any of Harbinger's rifts.

description: Creates a spirit link between Death Prophet and an enemy unit, draining 14 + 1.0 / 2.5 / 4.0 / 5.5% Max HP per second and steal %movement_slow% movement speed from the enemy.
language.lore: Krobelus willingly shows others the path she alone cannot follow.
notes: Cannot cast multiple on same target.

description: Lone Druid and the Spirit Bear roar fiercely causing nearby enemies to flee towards their base in terror. Their movement speed is increased by 20%.
notes: An entangled hero will not be able to move.
Cooldown is shared with Lone Druid.

description: This creature protects its allies with a Magic resistance aura. Creeps are better protected.
The Black Dragon hurls a fire blast on the ground, igniting the area in a 300 radius for 10.0 seconds. Enemies caught in the fire will take 85 damage per second.
Improves all attributes per point spent
Faceless Void traps all nearby enemies in a time dilation field for 8 / 10 / 12 / 14 seconds, extending their cooldowns and slowing their movement and attack speed by 10% for each cooldown extended.
language.lore: For those facing off against Darkterror, each moment seems to stretch into eternity.
notes: Does not affect item cooldowns.

description: Monkey King enlarges his staff and slams it against the ground, stunning enemies in a line and damaging them with a critical hit based on his attack. Has True Strike.
language.lore: The legendary Jingu Bang grows to match its master's will, ensuring no enemy can escape the Monkey King's reach.
notes: Does not affect spell-immune enemies.

description: Changes Monkey King's shape to deceive opponents, using the environment nearby as inspiration for the disguise. Taking damage, attacking, or using any item or ability breaks Monkey King's disguise. Grants damage immunity for 0.2 upon transforming.
language.lore: Watch out for that tree.
notes: If transformed into a courier, Monkey King matches the movement speed of the courier.

description: Monkey King jumps to a tree and perches atop it. While perched, he gains the Primal Spring ability-a channeled leap attack. If Monkey King's tree is destroyed, he falls and is stunned for 4 seconds. Taking damage from player controlled units or Roshan while on the ground puts Tree Dance on cooldown.
language.lore: Sun Wukong dances nimbly along the treetop canopy, always just out of arm's reach.
notes: Tree Dance cooldown starts upon landing.
Right-clicking the ground will have Monkey King drop from the tree.

description: Reverts Monkey King's shape to his original form.
Monkey King's attacks awaken the Jingu Bang's power. Upon the fourth hit on the same enemy hero, Monkey King earns four charged attacks that have bonus damage and lifesteal.
language.lore: Always sensitive to the moods of its master, the Jingu Bang radiates power when Sun Wukong's combat fervor is on full display.
notes: Hitting an enemy with Boundless Strike adds to the hit counter.
Repeatedly hitting an enemy refreshes the Jingu Mastery debuff duration.
Hit charges on enemies cannot be dispelled.

description: Monkey King springs out from his tree perch, damaging and slowing enemies in the area where he lands. Damage and slow amounts are in proportion to channel duration.
language.lore: Leaping from the safety of cover into the midst of his enemies, Sun Wukong attacks without mercy.

description: Monkey King creates a circular formation of soldiers that spread out from his position. If Monkey King leaves the area his soldiers disperse. The soldiers have Monkey King's attack and only target heroes. Monkey King is granted bonus armor for the spell's duration.
language.lore: Monkey King rips out a tuft of fur to blow at his enemies, charging each strand to transform into a copy of himself.
language.aghanimDescription: Spawns a monkey soldier near you at regular intervals. Soldiers do not spawn while invisible or on trees. Soldiers only attack buildings when Monkey King himself is nearby.
notes: Soldiers do not receive Jingu Mastery bonuses.
Soldiers do not copy Basher or Abyssal.

description: Reduces all elements to their basic levels, removing base armor and magic damage resistance from nearby enemy units. The armor reduction is centered around the hero, while the magic armor reduction is centered around Astral Spirit.
language.lore: As it was at the beginning, Elder Titan makes it so again.
notes: When the Astral Spirit isn't present, both the armor and magic armor reduction is centered around Elder Titan.

language.displayName: 80% Magic Resistance for Chaotic Offering Golems

description: Releases 12 Deafening Blasts around Invoker in a circular pattern.  An enemy can only be hit once per cast.
Gives lifesteal and health regeneration to nearby allies.
notes: The aura is stacking.

description: Automatically targets additional enemy units with a mana pool within 400 distance around the original target.
The duration of the stun is not affected.
Launches a two extra Stifling Daggers towards random visible enemies within the cast range.
Generates an aura that provides increased health and mana regeneration to nearby allies when activated.
notes: Right click the Shrine to activate.
Regeneration values increase by +2/1 health/mana per minute.
Additionally restores 2% health/mana pool per second.

description: The extra arrows are launched in a cone shape, 30 degrees to the left and right of the original arrow, and cannot hit the same target.
Stomps the ground, dealing damage to nearby units and reducing their base physical armor by 50%.
Causes the next attack to petrify the enemy, rooting them and dealing 75 damage per second.

language.displayName: Attacks Apply 60% MS and AS Slow

description: Allied heroes within 1200 range of Centaur gain the Return Damage aspect of Retaliate.
Creates a storm cloud anywhere on the map that automatically casts Lightning Bolt on nearby enemies.
language.lore: Where the thunder god's ire grows, storm clouds quickly gather.
notes: Grants 100 gold if destroyed by an enemy hero.
Affects the closest enemy unit with strikes from Zeus's current level of Lightning Bolt.
Towers and creeps do half damage to the Nimbus.

description: Dark Willow creates a maze of brambles that grow in the target area after 0.5 seconds. Enemies that walk into a bramble are rooted and take damage over time.
language.lore: The fae realm exists all around you, merely waiting to draw you in...
notes: Does not reveal rooted invisible enemies.
Does not interrupt channeling spells upon rooting.

description: Dark Willow's pet wisp roams around her for the duration, rapidly attacking nearby enemies.  Bedlam cannot be used while Terrorize is active.
language.lore: You'll have to excuse my friend Jex. He's really into murder.

description: Dark Willow recedes into the shadows, becoming untargetable. Her next attack has increased attack range and deals bonus magic damage, and will end Shadow Realm. Damage scales based on how long she remains under the effects of Shadow Realm, the maximum being reached after 3.5 seconds.
language.lore: What you can't see will most definitely hurt you.
language.aghanimDescription: Attacking no longer takes you out of Shadow Realm. Each attack still has bonus damage based on the duration of the buff.
notes: Disjoints projectiles upon cast.
Grants phased movement.
Spells which require vision cannot affect Dark Willow in the Shadow Realm.

description: Dark Willow casts an ancient fae curse on the target. After a delay, the target and nearby enemies are stunned.
language.lore: Didn't anyone ever tell you? Never strike a deal with a fairy...

description: Pangolier curls into a spell-immune ball and rolls out. When rolling, he moves at an increased speed and can move through trees, but has a decreased ability to turn. Striking enemies knocks them back, inflicting damage and stunning them when they land.
Colliding with walls or cliffs will cause a temporary pause while Pangolier reverses in direction.
DISPEL TYPE: Basic Dispel
language.lore: Where his ancestors sought only refuge, the Pangolier saw opportunity...
notes: Enemies can be stunned multiple times per use, but cannot be affected a subsequent time until the previous stun duration ends.
If Pangolier is disabled while rolling, he will continue to stun and knock enemies that come within range.

description: Vector Targeted. Pangolier dashes along the target line, then slashes all enemies in the drawn direction with several quick swipes.
Lucky Shot has a chance to activate from this damage.
language.lore: The Pangolier's blade is even nimbler than his tongue.
notes: Attack modifiers have a chance to proc on Swashbuckle attacks.
Casting Swashbuckle during Rolling Thunder ends Rolling Thunder.

description: Pangolier reads his enemies perfectly, deftly slipping his blade past defenses. Each attack has a chance to negate enemy armor and slow the target for a duration, activating after a short delay.
language.lore: These fools know nothing of real armor...
notes: Does not proc when attacking Roshan or buildings.

language.displayName: -0.1 Eye of the Storm Strike Interval

description: Halt!
language.lore: Donté Panlin stops when he pleases.

description: Pangolier jumps in the air and slams back to the ground in front of his current position, damaging all enemies in a radius. For each enemy hero hit, he gains a percentage of incoming damage reduction for a short time.
Forward movement is maintained if Shield Crash is used while Rolling Thunder is active, and allows Rolling Thunder to clear walls or cliffs.
language.lore: Only in the midst of his enemies does the Pangolier truly thrive.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes Shield Crash to cast a 2-attack Swashbuckle in every 90 degrees around your hero.

description: Void Spirit temporarily fades into the aether, creating a number of portals through which he can reassemble himself. Upon exiting a portal, he damages all enemies in the area.
language.lore: Inai much prefers to observe our plane free from the confines of corporeal form.

description: Snapfire unloads with a wide blast that damages and slows enemies in a cone. Enemies caught at point-blank range take an extra 50.0% damage.
language.lore: A favorite from her collection, Beadie crafted Ol' Rackatee as her first line of defense when she ventured into the Outlands.

description: Snapfire's friend launches a barrage of firespit globs over 6.0 seconds. Globs cause impact damage and create pools of firespit, which slow and apply damage over time. Snapfire has a reduced turn rate for the duration and a minimum launch range of 600. Each glob can be targeted with a right click.
language.lore: Little did Beadie know when she adopted Mortimer, dragon toads--which aren't even toads at all--share more than just a name with their distant draconic cousins.
notes: Can be cancelled by pressing Stop, Hold Position, or using another ability.
Has a minimum travel time of 0.8 and maximum travel time of 2.0.

description: Snapfire feeds a potent cookie to Mortimer or an ally, causing them to hop a short distance. The hopping unit stuns and damages enemies in the landing zone.
language.lore: With the help of a secret mixture that pairs Beadie's baking skills with her passion for black powder, these battle biscuits pack a punch.
notes: The cookie projectile has a speed of 1000.

description: Mortimer gobbles up a creep or an allied hero, which he can then spit towards enemies. The unit stays in his belly up to 3.0 seconds.
notes: Snapfire earns the creep's bounty after it has been spat out and died.

description: Mortimer spits out the unit that's in his mouth, causing impact damage and stun in a large area. The glob leaves a pool of firespit that slows and applies damage over time.
Snapfire heats up her mounted turret to rapidly fire 6 fixed-damage attacks. Each attack reduces the enemy's armor. Provides bonus attack range for the duration.
language.lore: Beadie constantly tinkers with a design she first dreamed up plotting an exodus from her old gang.
notes: Sets 1.0 base attack rate for the duration.
Attack modifiers have a chance to proc on Lil' Shredder attacks.

description: Binds a targeted enemy hero to its nearest allied hero within the bind radius, preventing both from moving away from each other. Any unit-targeted ability that either bound hero receives also gets cast on the other hero. If the bind is broken before the duration expires, the initial target will be bound to its nearest allied hero in the radius.
language.lore: The Ascended were chosen sons of Ashkavor, granted immense power by the bonds forged between their own souls and those they were charged with protecting. In the years that followed the ruination of his kin, Grimstroke discovered much more sinister applications for the binding rituals...
language.aghanimDescription: Grants you a new ability, Dark Portrait. Creates an ink illusion of a target enemy hero.
notes: Affected units are leashed, and prevented from blinking.
Provides vision of both leashed units.

description: Mars smashes enemies in front of him with his shield, knocking them back and damaging them with a critical hit based on his attack. Bonus damage is added when hitting heroes. Has True Strike.
language.lore: There isn't a warrior alive who can stand unmoved by the sting of Mars' rebuke.
language.aghanimDescription: Decreases cooldown of God's Rebuke.
notes: Attack modifiers have a chance to proc on God's Rebuke attacks.

description: A second Soul Assumption is launched towards a random enemy unit within the cast range, prioritizing Heroes.
Instead of being slowed, all enemy units within 900 range have the current level of Wraithfire Blast cast on them when Reincarnation triggers.

Mars wields his massive shield to block a portion of each physical attack when hit from the front or sides.

Can be toggled, removing Mars's ability to attack, and locking the direction he is facing. When active, reduces movement speed and re-directs 70% of the attack projectiles aimed at Mars's allies towards Mars instead.
language.lore: Only the very foolish dare to fight fair with the god of war.

description: Mars throws his legendary Spear with deadly precision, damaging each enemy unit it strikes. The first enemy hero it hits is skewered on the spear, pushing it back. If a skewered hero hits a tree, building, or cliff, they will be impaled to it and stunned.
language.lore: The legendary Spear of Mars still glows with the heat of the forge god's fires.
notes: Spear of Mars can hit invisible units and reveals them if they are stunned.
Spear of Mars will only pin a units to cliffs onto elevated areas, otherwise it will push them off onto lower ground.

description: After a short formation time, Mars summons an arena lined with the undead warriors of the Ash Legion, who block enemy attacks and movement. Enemy heroes near the inside edge of the arena will be attacked by spears, dealing damage and knocking them back.
language.lore: The long-dead members of the Ash Legion, assembled from the finest warriors to ever test the might of Mars, still revel in the thrill of combat, gladly beholden to the hand that fell them for as long as he so commands.

description: When using Searing Arrows, a second Searing Arrow targets a random enemy within the spell's range.
Launched when Sun Strike is double tapped. Puts it on a 90 second cooldown. Creates 2 visible Sun Strikes within 160-200 range of each enemy hero.
Spawns 3 Ghostships, 3.35 seconds apart, towards the target location.
Additional enemy units within cast range are also targeted by Adaptive Strike.

language.displayName: +80 Hunter In The Night Attack Speed
Arena Of Blood Grants Team +80 HP Regen

description: After blinking, an uncontrollable illusion is created at Anti-Mage's original location.  Deals -80% less damage, takes 250% damage, and lasts 10 seconds.
Allows on-hit effects to apply to the secondary attacks from Split Shot.
While Exorcism is active, Death Prophet moves at 550 movement speed and cannot be slowed.
While tethered to a friendly Hero, each time that Hero attacks, Io will attack the same target automatically.
Your own attacks against enemy units also have a chance to trigger Counter Helix.
Bane gains attack speed equal to the attack speed stolen for the duration of Enfeeble.
Enemies hit by Waveform are also instantly attacked by Morphling.
Puck instantly attacks all enemies while affected by Dream Coil, every 0.75 seconds.
Enemies damaged by Scream of Pain are forced to run towards their fountain for 1.2 seconds.

language.displayName: +180 Eye of the Storm Passive Damage

description: No actions take Riki out of invisibility, only revealed by sources of True Sight.

language.displayName: 600 Distance Auto Remnant in Ball Lightning
description: Every 600 distance travelled in Ball Lightning creates a Static Remnant.
Applies a basic dispel on all enemies hit.
While tethered to a friendly Hero, that Hero gains its Aghanim's Scepter ability upgrades for the duration.
Throws the tree at the target unit, proccing your attack on it and splashing damage around the target.
language.lore: Even enemies can share in Tiny's arbor ardor.

description: Applies a basic dispel to Templar Assassin.
Enemies hit by the spill of Psi Blades have their movement speed slowed by 100% for 1.0 second.
Any tree that is destroyed on the map will respawn 2 seconds later.
Can be cast while stunned and applies a strong dispel to Troll Warlord.
Walrus Punch gains a chance to be triggered on normal attacks, independent of mana cost or cooldown.
The target of False Promise also becomes invisible for the duration (with a 0.6 second fade time).
The wards are based on the current level of Plague Ward and spawned within 100 range of the impacted Hero, on opposite sides.
The slow is still applied for the same duration.
All mines, including Stasis Traps, can be ordered to move to a location once placed.

Launches a surge of water toward an enemy unit, stunning and knocking back the target based on Morphling's strength. If his strength is 50% higher than his agility, the maximum stun/knockback is dealt.
Also puts Adaptive Strike (Agility) on a 3 second cooldown.
language.lore: The Morphling calls upon his elements to crush his opponents with waves.
notes: Projectile moves at 1150 speed.

description: Grants a 20% chance to avoid damage entirely.
Toss can target the ground as well as enemy units.
Creates an additional ring of 7 soldiers at 1100 range from the center.
A second Wall of Replica is created 600 units behind the first wall.  Illusions are independent for each Wall.

language.displayName: Soul Catcher Creates 2 Illusion On Death

description: Affects visible units only.

After a short delay, the nearest Familiar turns into stone and smashes into the ground, stunning and damaging all targets in the area. The Familiar becomes invulnerable, and will regain its health very rapidly. After 6.0 seconds, the Familiar will automatically leave Stone Form.
notes: While Stone Form is not dispellable, the stun can be removed by strong dispells.

description: Pierces Spell Immunity.
Beastmaster calls forth a Boar to aid in the battlefield.
language.lore: After befriending the strange beast of his childhood, Beastmaster has learned to call to animals in times of need.

description: Beastmaster sends an invisible Hawk to scout an area.
language.lore: After befriending the strange beast of his childhood, Beastmaster has learned to call to animals in times of need.

description: In a fiery rage, knocks all nearby enemies away from you to a fixed distance, dealing damage and disarming them.
language.lore: Not even Huskar's own flesh can contain the unending expansion of his life force.

description: Spirit Breaker gains movement speed and status resistance to ram through enemies. Can be used while charging.
language.lore: Barathrum warps the fabric of reality around him, lessening its influence on his physical form.

description: Passively reduces cooldowns on your abilities and items. Anytime you cast a spell, all nearby enemies will have their armor reduced. Debuff stacks and refreshes duration.
language.lore: Each invocation of the Nothl realm helps it further permeate the surroundings of our own.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes all of your abilities to fire an attack at nearby enemies when they are cast.

description: Passively provides an aura that grants increased health regeneration and amplifies all health restore by a percentage.
Can be cast on allies to teleport them to Chen. If cast on Chen, all units controlled by Chen will be teleported to him. Taking damage will dispel the buff.
language.lore: Chen's zeal is infectious, blessing his allies with vitality and compelling them to his side.

description: Pangolier rolls the dice and lets fate decide the outcome for his enemies. Grants a chance to slow, apply a Disarm and reduce armor.
language.lore: The Pangolier's blade is guided more often by whim than reason.

description: Spirit Bear absorbs 30% of the damage dealt to Lone Druid.
Links Lone Druid and the Spirit Bear, increasing the attack speed of both and causing damage dealt by the Spirit Bear to heal Lone Druid.
language.lore: Sylla is emboldened by the presence of his companion, his vitality replenished with each swipe of the Spirit Bear's claws.

description: Drenches an area in alcohol, causing enemy units to move slower and ignited once they take any spell damage. Duration is increased by 3 seconds when ignited.
language.lore: The Order of the Oyo's solution to all problems - another round!

description: Grants you bonus attack speed for a limited number of attacks, draining a percentage of mana for each hit. Costs a percentage of current health to cast. Lasts up to 15 seconds or when the attack count is consumed.
Allied Aura. Causes all nearby ally attacks to slow enemy movement speed.
Passively grants you magic resistance. Can be activated to create an anti-magic shell around you that sends any targeted spells back towards enemies instead of affecting you.
language.lore: With the proper focus, Anti-Mage turns innate resistance into calculated retaliation.

description: Summons Ignis Fatuus at the targeted area. Alternates on and off every second. When actived, it causes all enemies near it to stare hypnotized at it. Can be attacked by units in or outside of the radius, dies after a certain number of attacks.
language.lore: Though he would not claim to 'know' them, Ezalor holds an uncanny influence over many powerful creatures always willing to come to his aid.

description: Steals health from the enemy with each strike and heals all other Meepos for that amount.
language.lore: So you gonna need that, or...?

description: Clinkz summons an army of fiery ranged skeleton archers. Archers are immobile and die with 2 attacks from a hero. Skeletons deal a percentage of Clinkz' damage, use his current Searing Arrows ability and attack only heroes. Attack range is equal to Clinkz's attack range.
language.lore: Existing on the brink of life and death, Clinkz has learned to temporarily bridge the gap between the two.

description: Rubick's mastery of the arcane allows him to deal more spell damage and create spells that last longer on enemies.
language.lore: Not every magus can be a Grand Magus...

description: Temporarily applies a negative debuff aura around you, causing enemies that are attacked under it to take bonus physical damage and reduced movement speed. Lasts 5 seconds.
language.lore: Even far from Cobalt, Tusk carries the 'Barrier Chill' in his very bones.
notes: Affects attacks from allied heroes, Tusk or any of his units.

description: Causes affected enemies to deal less spell damage for a duration.
language.lore: When faced with the pit of sacrifice, Purist's resilience to magic was tested and affirmed.

description: CHANNELED - Hypnotizes an enemy unit, causing it to move towards a point between the two of you and drains a percentage of its current mana.
language.lore: Mind the cold...
language.aghanimDescription: Casts Sinister Gaze in a target area.

description: Vector targeted. Void Spirit dispatches a remnant to the target location. The remnant stands watch over the region, facing the direction of his vector. When a unit crosses its gaze, the remnant pulls it in and damages it.
language.lore: Inai exists far beyond the scope of a single point in space and time.

description: Void Spirit tears a rift through the astral plane to appear at the target location, attacking all enemies along the path. This attack inflicts a void mark that slows for 1.25 seconds and then detonates.
language.lore: A small step for Inai creates great devastation on the mortal plane.
notes: Astral Step attacks do not cleave.

description: Void Spirit wraps himself in a protective shield that absorbs physical damage and emits a single damaging pulse around him. The shield gains increased damage absorption for each enemy hero the pulse hits.
language.lore: Inai never hesitates to shroud himself in the essence of his true self when forced to interact with the mortal plane.
language.aghanimDescription: Causes Resonant Pulse to silence and gain two charges.
